name: WinOps London - DevOps on Windows
description:
The UK's first dedicated meetup and conference on 'Windows in a DevOps World'.

Join us for our launch on the 22nd Sept 2015 for the first #WinOps event exploring and promoting DevOps on Windows.

In this group we will be exploring and sharing experiences of using products and tools within the Microsoft DevOps world such as:

PowerShell, TeamCity, Octopus Deploy, Azure, Vagrant, Chocolatey, AppDynamics, ScriptRock, Chef, Puppet, Ansible, Docker etc.

Please feel free to join our community!

www.winops.org

Please also follow us on twitter for updates, @WinOpsLDN

name: LJC - London Java Community
description:
The London Java Community (LJC) is a group of Java Enthusiasts who are interested in benefiting from shared knowledge in the industry. Through our forum and regular meetings you can keep in touch with the latest industry developments, learn new Java (& other JVM) technologies, meet other developers, discuss technical/non technical issues and network further throughout the Java Community.

FAQ

What is the LJC?

What goes on in the LJC?

Who can join?

Is there a fee to Join, is there a fee for the events?

How do I join?

Do you have to go to every presentation?

Where are the events held?

Can I read some member feedback?

What is the LJC?

The LJC is an official Java User Group for developers based in London. It  was founded in November 2007 and since then has grown to over 5000 members and is now the biggest Java User Group in the UK.


What goes on in the LJC?

We run a variety of regular events ranging from social events and technical presentations to our full day unconference. On top of the events we run prize draws and have an active mailing list/forum. We support the Graduate Development Community in London and promote London based Open Source Software projects where possible.

Who can join?

Membership is restricted to Java developers working in or around London (or those hoping to train in Java, or relocate to London). Membership will not be granted to those involved in the recruitment industry.


Is there a fee to Join, is there a fee for the events?

It’s completely free to join and 99% of our events are completely free. The only event which is charged for is the Unconference, the charge is minimal and it is there to cover refreshments on the day.


How do I join?

Just click on the link on this page to sign up to the mailing list, you'll hear of all of our latest news and events and can take part in the monthly prize draws.

Do you have to go to every presentation?

Absolutely not – it’s completely up to you which events you attend and which you don’t. Every event attracts a different crowd.


Where are the events held?

Europe's Premier technical training company, Skills Matter (Barbican) sponsor most of our events by providing the venue.

Can I read some member feedback?

We have been collecting feedback for the last few years from our members you can read it here: http://www.meetup.com/Londonjavacommunity/about/comments/?op=all

For further information see our blog here: http://londonjavacommunity.co.uk/ Do not hesitate to get in touch with any questions.

Barry Cranford
Founder of London Java Community

name: Kubernetes London
description:
Meet other engineers interested in Google Kubernetes. 

Kubernetes is an open source system for managing containerized applications across multiple hosts, providing basic mechanisms for deployment, maintenance, and scaling of applications. 

Kubernetes builds upon a decade and a half of experience at Google running production workloads at scale, combined with best-of-breed ideas and practices from the community.

name: data+visual London
description:
data+visual is a group for anyone interested in the world of data visualisation. Meet other people generating insight from data, share your work, knowledge and get feedback from others. We are tech & tool agnostic: the main focus is on the journey that happens from raw data to resulting story. 

Meeting topics are varied and range from tutorials on basic concepts and their applications, to discussions on tools, new technologies, and best practices. At each meeting we have lightning talks where people showcase their latest projects and then we have a longer talk where someone walks through a specific topic.

name: Real-Time Enterprise Orchestration and Automation
description: Special interest group for those involved in automating the enterprise to rise to the new challenges facing by the imminent emergence of the Real-Time Enterprise. We promote discussion on challenges and solutions exchange. We arrange sponsored events, round tables, and web conferences for invite only member discussions.

name: London Web
description:
The meetup where people listen. We cut back the noise and focus on people who can teach us, interact with us, and help us learn from being around other like-minded people. Events often have multiple streams that relate to web design and development.

Who should come:

    web designers and front-end pixel pushers

    back-end developers

    graphic designers involved in designing for the web

    web entrepreneurs

    web investors

We focus on the future - the future is bright!

Join us on the third Thursday of every month.

name: London Object Storage Enthusiasts
description: This Group is eager to learn and share experiences that relate to Designing, Building, Managing, & Operating Massively Scalable Storage Infrastructure for Today's Web Service Applications in the Data Center.

name: Ansible London
description: We are group of Systems Engineers and DevOps folks who want to Ansible all the things. Want to learn more about Ansible? Come join us. Already know Ansible well? Come share your knowledge.

name: Scalability London
description:
Enterprise or Start-up?

Capacity and scaling of applications, systems and teams to support business needs can be challenging. We'd like to meet up quarterly  to share problems, ideas and solutions. 

Are you:

Running an internal cloud or want to run an internal cloud? 

Monitoring 1000's of servers and services or need to run 1000's of servers and services? 

Building a website for millions of users?

Someone else is doing it already and what's to share how they did it. Let's get together, have a chat and maybe a beer or two!

name: Data Visualisation with Tableau
description: We have no scheduled meet ups yet arranged we want to gauge interest first. Once we have a few people interested we will sort out a meeting

name: Trendwise Research London
description: I'm hosting an open working group for data scientists looking to collaborate on conducting large scale trend research using new methods of analysis such as TrendCalculus. Open to all researchers and data science practitioners, of any discipline, and all skill sets. There is much to do. The idea is to run an active, collaborative open research group both online and with meetups, where we will review progress, and present findings.

name: London PaaS & Bluemix Meetup
description: This is an IBM sponsored PaaS meetup group. Geared towards developers, architects and all Bluemix enthusiasts, we learn about Bluemix hands on with fellow developers. Learn how to use this new PaaS product with the current apps. Our meetups are free.

name: Looker User Group – London Area
description: Welcome to our burgeoning community of Looker users in the greater London area. Each meetup typically showcases several Looker implementations at businesses (like yours?) that rely on data to succeed. Users present a specific use case, an interesting path to insights, or maybe an overview of Looker adoption throughout the organization. It’s also a good time to eat, drink, and network with others who are using Looker to explore data. You will get the address to the next Meetup, after you become a member. Email elena@looker.com if you have any questions.

name: London Digital Analytics
description:
This group is for anybody in Digital or Web Analytics irrespective of which tool you use:

e.g. Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, Omniture, Webtrends, Coremetrics, Optimist, Maxymiser practitioners and/or users involved in AB or MVT testing, Conversion Rate Optimisation (CRO) and all other measurement related digital things!

It does not matter which sector or size of your company – please feel free to come along!  We are a real mix of experienced analytics practioners and people who want to learn what web analytics is plus everything in between.

We keep this meetup fairly informal.  There are no big presentations with a short Q&A.  Definitely no sales pitches.  Instead we encourage discussions and for people to ask questions which others answer.  The more knowledge being shared the better.  Come and join us in our discussions, whether you have more questions to ask or answers to share. 

Meetups are now held at WeWork offices around London.  WeWork is the platform for creators. We provide the space, community and services you need to create your life’s work. To learn more about WeWork's upcoming locations in London, send an email to joinus@wework.com and let them know you were referred by London Digital Analytics meetup.

name: Dis-Functional
description: This is a group for anyone interested in big data, DISTRIBUTED COMPUTING and FUNCTIONAL PROGRAMMING (DIS-FUNCTIONAL). You see the challenges that come from offering a complete streaming solution for businesses. Libraries such as akka-stream and scalaz-stream provide compositional API's for processing streams on single nodes, while Apache Spark Streaming provides a multi-node solution for (mini-batched) stream processing. Moroever, Apache Kafka is a scalable solution for getting all those precious streams safely on and off disk. If this sounds interesting, stick around.

name: London MongoDB User Group
description: This group is a place for developers to learn more about the non-relational, open source, document-oriented database MongoDB. MongoDB is the leading NoSQL database and many of the key committers often travel to London. So if you are facing challenges with MySQL or Postgres or Oracle and want to explore a more flexible, scalable alternative, please join us at one of our monthly sessions.

name: Paper Cup
description: Paper Cup is a Computer Science Papers Reading Club. We pick interesting papers, read them at home and discuss at meetings.

name: HackWimbledon
description:
TL;DR: HackWimbledon is a pop-up hack space for makers and creators, held in Wimbledon and hosted by WimbleTech.

They say the future is in the hands of the makers, the creators. Hackers are the digital makers and creators and they now have a whole range of new tools to build things with from tiny electronics to minicomputers, from Raspberry Pis to Arduinos and many others you won’t have heard of. 

They are all out there ready to be wired into whatever you want them to be and programmed to make them do what you want them to do. But where do you start if you want to make a web-connected thermometer, a simple robot, an energy saving light or a weather aware window? 

This is what HackWimbledon wants to illuminate. HackWimbledon meets up every other Saturday @ Wimbletech, in Wimbledon library (5 minutes Wimbledon station, a home for startups and coworkers in Merton!).  HackWimbledon runs from 11am to 4pm. If you want to take part, turn up. If you want to hack, bring a laptop. 

Our resident curator, @codepope, is always on hand to show the various gadgets you can bend to your will. We’ll have some boards to play with and assistance to get you going. Each meeting has a challenge for new and experienced hackers, a curators corner with something interesting being built or programmed and, of course, space for you to work on your own project in a supportive and fun environment. 

HackWimbledon is aimed at supporting you and the hacking and creating community. So come along and join in - you too can make, create and illuminate at HackWimbledon!

name: C++ London Developers Meetup
description:
This group exists for professional C++ programmers developing for just about any device!

Mobile, desktop, OSX, Linux, Windows, embedded, games consoles, gaming..........you name it.

This group brings together like minded developers whatever you code, with a central focus to swap ideas, stories, skills, and network.

name: DeNormalised London
description:
Data is growing in size and complexity. Increasing velocity, volume and variety of data are driving new database technologies and techniques of data analysis. NOSQL databases are becoming more popular and widely accepted. This is leading to a disruption in the database market and a fragmentation of database solutions.

At DeNormalised we want to bring together people who are interested in keeping up to date with the evolving landscape of data persistance and analysis. Our meetups will consist of a number of short talks on a range of topics including NOSQL, big data and data science.

The meetups are designed to give broad exposure and inspire. If you build, maintain or manage software that produces data, there's a good chance you'll get something out of this group.

Come along, learn and share.

name: Cisco TechHuddle London Meetup
description: Cisco TechHuddle is an interactive tech update, for techies by techies – not a sales pitch or sales person in sight. We aim to update, educate and demo on the latest Cisco technologies, in an informal, interactive environment. There is also the opportunity to network and chat with your peers and Cisco experts

name: Technology and Finance
description:
Working in Finance and Technology can be quite demanding, yet very rewarding. We believe surrounding yourself with like-minded people is essential to your success and progress within your professional life. Technology and Finance Society is a not for profit initiative, which aims to help London FinTech, Cyber Security, Risk and Compliance professionals, entrepreneurs, start-ups and businesses to connect, collaborate and Evolve.

Since 2013 Technology and Finance Society (T&F) has been working with the help of its +1200 members on developing a Collaborative knowledge share platform and growth support network. This allow society members to meet monthly to discuss new and emerging trends, share knowledge and experience, and show case their work and collaborate on developing it.

The society uses a number of different social media channels to reach out to the wider Technology and Finance community. This LinkedIn group is our newest social media channel and we hope it will be our main knowledge share and collaborative platform, till the launch of the society interactive website.

Follow us on Twitter and connect with fellow members on LinkedIn.

name: CloudStack European User Group
description: A group of like minded Cloud professionals focusing on Cloudstack; regular physical meetings throughout Europe .

name: Venture Hack Network
description: The Venture Hack Network is a community for entrepreneurs, intended to help them accelerate their startup ideas through collaborative ‘growth hacking‘,

name: Artists and Scientists Get-Together (London)
description: Science and art both rely on observation and synthesis: taking what is seen and creating something new from it. Our society could hardly exist without either, but when they come together our culture is enriched, sometimes in unexpected ways....

name: Big Data Week London Meetup
description: Big Data Week is one of the most unique global platforms of interconnected community events focusing on the social, political, technological impacts of Data. It brings together a global community of data scientists, data technologies, data visualisers and data businesses spanning six major commercial, financial, social and technological sectors. This is our official meetup group.

name: Hands-on Big data science workshop
description: Come with your laptop, and learn or help to build big data science applications on your computer using the hadoop/yarn ecosystem. Main tools/frameworks on the map at the moment : H2O, Spark, docker, arduino, PIG, HBASE, Phoenix, Storm, deep learning ,real time analytics , graph analytics, virtualization, baysian nets, churn analysis, outlier detection....

name: London Tech Job Fair Meetup
description:
Calling all coding ninjas, iOS developers, Android developers, internet marketing experts, SEO, digital marketing, PHP developers, Lamp developers, symphony, hadoop, node.js, bigdata, mongodb, parse, SDK, API, Java Developers, MySQL, Oracle and ERP, email marketing experts, bloggers, recruiters, career advice providers, employers to all come together, meet and share knowledge, information on tech city London updates, guide and share in-depth knowledge on industry relevant topics & trends, new technology, motivate job seekers and help out each other.

Drinks & Events Sponsored by http://TechCitySkills.com - post startup jobs for free & http://Appsjunction.net - connect with App devs.

name: Society of Data Miners
description:
The Society of Data Miners (SocDM, see http://www.socdm.org) is an independent non-profit organisation for the public good with the purposes to:

• Increase the benefits of data mining to society;

• Increase knowledge and awareness of the nature and benefits of data mining;

• Advance the profession of data mining;

• Form a community of and for data miners.

In pursuit of these purposes, the Society of Data Miners will:

• Hold events for data miners to exchange experience, formulate best practice and broaden the scope and benefits of data mining;

• Encourage adoption of the highest ethical standards in data mining;

• Provide public and media information about data mining and its benefits;

• Provide certification of data miners who have reached a recognised level of competence and experience in data mining practice;

• Encourage the creation of a literature of data mining practice;

• Encourage data mining standards;

• Encourage the teaching of data mining practice in educational institutions.

name: London Julia User Group
description: Julia is a high-level, high-performance dynamic programming language for technical computing, with syntax that is familiar to users of other technical computing environments. It provides a sophisticated compiler, distributed parallel execution, numerical accuracy, and an extensive mathematical function library. Want to show what you are working on? Questions to ask? Want to meet others who are using Julia? Let's meetup and talk Julia!

name: Infosec, Risk & Compliance - London
description:
This group enables industry professionals to meet, network, exchange ideas and discuss the latest trends and developments with others in the information security community.

Respected subject matter expert guest speakers from all industries will deliver presentation talks on key issues, such as...

Cloud security

Risk management

Data protection

Business Continuity

Cybercrime

Data Breach Incident Management and Recovery

Web Application Security

Compliance Regulation and Standard

Secure Coding and Application Programming

Network Security Management

Endpoint Protection & BYOD

Identity & Access Management

name: London: The Future Of The Web
description:
* What your Meetup Group is about?

A group dedicated to discussing the future of web technologies. Bringing you the latest information, presentations and demonstrations on what is the next wave of cutting edge technology.


* Who should join:

Anyone that has a genuine interest in following and discussing the latest trends and technologies within the web development space.

* Why they should join: 

To learn, share, or have fun and stay ahead of the game!


* What members can expect: 

Lots of: Tech talk, beers, pizza's  and everything in between!

name: DevOps Playground
description:
Interested in DevOps? Confused about all the concept and tools out there? Our meetup group aims to provide some technical hands on with some of the emerging and popular DevOps tools. Our aim is to provide a platform to share and collaborate knowledge amongst all our members

The Groups Objectives are:

* To provide a community with practical hands on examples using some of the latest DevOps tools

* To meet like minded techies and share each others experiences

* To collaborate in an environment where we bring our ideas to life and learn how these technologies work

name: Smarter Cities - London
description:
Smarter London is a monthly grassroots multi-city salon for talking, demoing, sharing, case-studies, prototypes, applications, networks, best practices, investment/funding opportunities, successes and failures in projects or pilots involved in making our cities smarter and issues facing it.

We are starting in London and bringing this format to other cities interested in jointly building an inter-disciplinary tech, business, city and startup community interested in co-creating smarter cities with city officials, planners, tech service providers and community interest groups. If you are a developer, designer, investor, city planner, community expert, involved in public policy, urban data modeler, architect, startup looking at getting involved and connected to a budding entrepreniural smarter city community – this is your meetup. 

Find us at @D4SC on Twitter and use #SmarterLondon for interesting pilots, projects, people, funding opportunities, jobs or anything related to making London Smarter by involving people, technology, data and city systems both at grassroots and at scale. We want to bring big and little data together.

Get in touch with Priya  (@priyascape or priya dot prakash at design4socialchange dot com) if you’d like to share something with this community or to partner/sponsor one of our meetups – Currently exploring a number of spaces to run this meetup including Level 39.

name: London Functional Programmers
description: Connecting Functional Programming talent around the World. Bringing you the latest Functional Programming jobs - sign up now - https://jobs.functionalworks.com/ and start using Functional Programming everyday!

name: Scale Warriors of London
description:
Scale Warriors are engineers and entrepreneurs pushing the limits of speed at scale. They are pioneers, open to possibilities, doing what has not been done before. They are innovators and inventors, modern day heroes breaking barriers, taking risks, facing fears, making mistakes, moving forward moment by moment, creating a new future for themselves, their teams, their companies, for people and the planet.

This group brings Scale Warriors together to hear about challenges building real-time big data driven applications, discuss NoSQL and distributed databases, emerging technologies, what works, what doesn't and best practices for operating internet-scale systems.

Read Scale Warrior stories.

Find Us:

http://www.aerospike.com


Follow Us:

https://twitter.com/aerospikedb


https://www.linkedin.com/company/2696852


http://www.youtube.com/user/AerospikeTV

name: HyperLedger (London Chapter)
description:
Does The Hyperledger Project have the potential to become the engine behind most successful decentralized applications and organizations created in the next 25-50 years? Absolutely!

A much better question is how, and in what new ways, can we:

a) Build decentralized applications, organizations and APIs at 10x the speed at 1/10 the cost.

b) Build situational awareness in the local community.

I believe that the convergence of decentralized applications, decentralized organizations, artificial intelligence and IoT brings upon us the Great Displacement of the 21st century, where the majority of workforce will be left without “conventional” jobs, forced to learn new skills and professions.

Why?

Founders of this group believe that the Hyperledger Foundation will be the engine behind decentralization of the world, a massive economic change of the next 25-50 years.

So.... why don't we standardize and democratize the field with and around Hyperledger?

What?

We are a local micro community of those interested in advancing their knowledge of Hyperledger, its use cases and applications.

How?

Join our group for a regular dose of human interaction, conversations, smiles, food and drinks on all things Hyperledger:

• Use Cases

• Competitive analysis of Hyperledger startups (Distributed Apps from disruptive companies in specific vertical markets)

• How-To’s

• Interviews with individuals working at the edge of the Hyperledger project

• Reviews of tools, services and APIs offered by the Hyperledger ecosystem

• Best Practices in Application Architecture

• Do’s and Don’ts

• Application Templates

• Hackathons

• Security in the decentralized world - on the edge, on the node, in the cloud and in transit

• How others solve some of the hard problems that exist in the world using Hyperledger.


Join the movement. Let’s change the world. Because with Hyperledger we can.

https://www.hyperledger.org/

https://github.com/hyperledger

name: Data Plus Women
description: This group exists to celebrate and advance the achievements and accomplishments by women in data. Are you qualified to join? Are you a woman? Have a mother? A sister? A daughter? Work with women? Well, then you qualify. We hope that you'll participate in this open discussion on how to help advance women in data.

name: South England Natural Language Processing Meetup
description: Established in 2013, we are a monthly meeting between academic and industry Natural Language Processing enthusiasts. We are hosted by the University College London Machine Reading group and invite speakers located or visiting the South England area to give talks and discuss their work with us.

name: Advanced Data Visualisation London
description:
Practical and in-depth debates about data visualisation, advanced analytics and machine learning. Data scientists, BI analysts, statisticians, mathematicians and programmers are all welcome. Feel free to bring your visualisations to share and discuss with the community. Each meeting will feature two or three 30-minute talks followed by Q&As and networking - all in a lovely Soho office with snacks and drinks provided.  

We cover different types of algorithmic and computer generated visualisations of varied datasets. We don't coverer infographics, art and 3d modelling.

Would you like to take the floor? Please get in touch if: 

• you've done a research on visualisation, 

• you've coded/generated a stunning visualisation,

• your organisation has accumulated significant experience in data visualisation and is willing to share the best practices.

All slides are published here: https://speakerdeck.com/advanced_data_visua...

Join and enjoy!

name: Neo4j - London User Group
description:
Welcome to the London meetup for Neo4j, the world's leading graph database.  We think graph databases are the future of data storage, because it's so expressive to model interesting connected data in a graph and super fast to query too.

Every month we get together with our community (and customers) for fun and informative talk on Neo4J or graphs in general. Whether you're new to the world of graph databases or if you're an experienced graphista, everyone's welcome to join us for a drink afterwards and we pick up the tab. It's a great opportunity to network (see, graphs are everywhere!), and also to put those burning questions to the Neo4j engineering team over a pint.

 




Big thanks to Skills Matter for providing the venue.

name: Equal Experts Technical Meetup Group
description: Welcome to Equal Experts technical meetup group. Our aim is to bring together creative and innovative minds to further the discussions on current and emerging technologies, software engineering practices, agile technical practices and open source. Equal Experts is an award winning consultancy developing bespoke software for customers using Agile practices.

name: Eurostaff Connect - Big Data and Advanced Analytics
description: This is a group where people can get together and share any Big Data passions. All skill-levels are welcome and no idea/ topic will be ignored! Let's build a community that shares knowledge over a few after-work drinks, now and again. Organised by Isabella from Eurostaff.

name: Node Workshops
description:
This group will get together and go through various Node.js related topics. 

Amongst other topics, we intend to work though these workshops - http://nodeschool.io/#workshopper-list

Please get in touch if you can help out with a venue...

name: West London Salesforce1 Users and Developers
description: A group for new and existing Salesforce Users, Developers, Administrator to come together and learn about all the latest innovation happening in Cloud Computing, Salesforce, Mobile and Social CRM Space. Also an opportunity to meet the experts who can help answer your questions and provide support for your Journey with Salesforce1

name: I love 3D - London
description: For both web designers and software developers - 3D on the WEB Night – Modeling, VR, WebGL and Three.js - make 3D models even more immersive and engaging on the WEB

name: London Enterprise Linux Meetup
description:
Do you use Linux to run your business? 

Or are you working for a company that does? Interested in containers, virtualisation and cloud? 

Initially focused on the big three commercial distributions, join us as we:

• explore best practices and new developments

• trade 'stories from the trenches'. 

• explore the Linux and the open source world. 

Rather than be distribution specific, we've created this generic group as we know in a typical enterprise that there will be multiple flavours of Linux in use at any one time. And acknowledged as being the bedrock of the datacentre, you're almost certainly using it, or affected by it - even if you don't think that you are.

We aim to meet monthly for discussions in a Central London venue with ideally two or three talks followed by conversations and food.

Oh, And have fun and meet like-minded people! 

The use of our mailing list for recruitment, marketing, and advertisement is strictly forbidden.

Code of Conduct

All members are required to agree with the following code of conduct. All members of the community are expected to enforce this code at every event, with help from the organisers. We are expecting cooperation from all participants in the community to help ensuring a safe environment for everybody.

tl;dr: Be excellent with each other

Need Help?

The contact details of the organisers are on our website and in any emails we have sent.

The Quick Version

Our community is dedicated to providing a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of gender, age, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, or religion (or lack thereof). We do not tolerate harassment of community members in any form. Sexual language and imagery is not appropriate for any community event, including talks, workshops, parties, Twitter and other online media. Participants violating these rules may be sanctioned or expelled from the event and any future events without a refund (if applicable), or from the community itself, at the discretion of the organisers.

See the full version here...

name: Women in Data
description: This group is for women who love data; big or small. Whether you work in data or want to know what the fuss is all about. Let's get together to share experiences, learn and shout about our achievements. The group format will be directed by the needs of it's members. At whatever stage of your career and whatever your specialty be it a Statistician, Developer, Visualizer, Journalist or a little of everything we hope to have a place for everyone to develop. We hope to get women working on interesting challenges to speak about a variety of topics. If there are any topics you would specifically like to see discussed then please let us know. This is a group to help us better understand our craft but also to talk about wider issues of this new data age.

name: The Data Foundry
description:
Our Manifesto:

• Be True

• Everybody analyzes data -  no BI

• Use data to support your questions

• Connect multiple data chunks to get the real picture

• Right tool  / Right time / for Right People


The group is for all data enthusiastic people in London. Our mission is to enable people of all levels and backgrounds to easily prepare and explore their data, help them to find the answers and become data-driven. We love data, that's it!


Are you: 

- DATA GREENHORN, but you want to do something with it? 

- DATA ANALYST OR SCIENTIST and want to be always up to date?

- STARTUP FOUNDER and want to become data driven? 

- BUSINESSMAN who sees big value in data, which means $$$? 


JOIN US!

name: London Cloud Computing / NoSQL
description: Meet others in your local area interested in Cloud Computing/NoSQL.

name: All Hands on DevOps
description: All Hands on DevOps has been created as a London-centric monthly Meetup focused on DevOps as a methodology and platform for Engineers, Administrators, Architects, Leaders and Evangelists to share experiences of implementing DevOps into environments of various scales.

name: CiviCRM - London meetup group
description:
The meetup.com information page for the Official CiviCRM London meetups.

CiviCRM is an open source donor and constituent management solution for non profits and member organisations.

Meetups are a great way to:

  • network with the CiviCRM community
  • find out about how people are making the most out of CiviCRM
  • discover if CiviCRM is suitable for your organisation
  • learn about what is coming up in future releases

Meetups generally start at 6.00pm and finish about 8.30pm, but do come along earlier as we'll be there from 5.30pm.

At each meetup there will be an introduction to CiviCRM, a case study of an organisation using it and other presentations on great features of CiviCRM.

Really important!

The meetup.com page is for information only.

Please always remember to register at CiviCRM.org if you are intending on coming to the meetup, to make sure we can keep you up to date with the latest from the CiviCRM UK community.

Find the latest events here:

http://civicrm.org/civi-upcoming-events

name: London NoSQL
description:
A meet-up group to learn and chat about all data topics, from NoSQL technologies to big data techniques.

We're on Twitter, too: http://twitter.com/LondonNoSQL

name: London SAS User Group
description: This is a group for anyone interested in SAS development and use. All skills levels are welcome.

name: London Management Information Meetup
description: This is a group for business owners and decision makers to come together and figure out how to take advantage of data and analytics technology without becoming swamped by information. We'll meet monthly to talk about data systems integration, visualisation, dashboards, decision making and information sharing. The focus is on producing simple, understandable and actionable information that will help our businesses grow, using the latest and best technology tools and information design thinking.

name: London Spree Commerce User Group
description:
Share tools, tips, and war stories about using Spree Commerce, the open-source e-commerce platform built on Ruby-on-Rails.

We are very enthusiastic about Spree Commerce. We see this open-source tech as the future of E-Commerce that can help retailers and developers alike be able to build their platforms in a much smarter way, based on modern tech.

If you are a retailer who has felt pain in implementing E-com with traditional platforms in the past, or are just looking to innovate, or if you are a Ruby dev or E-com enthusiast looking to build E-com stores, then this user group is for you.

We're going to see how this first one starts off, maybe meet up quarterly to start and then slowly build the group to what will hopefully be a monthly meetup.

We want to do live demos, talks about Spree extensions people are building, talk about projects they have completed, allow people to share war stories and create opportunities to collaborate on fixing common problems. It is open-source after all!

We started this group because we genuinely feel that this can bring a new way of doing E-commerce to the forefront.

So, let's all have some fun over some beers and pizza, and grow the London spree to community, collaborating together and see where this platform goes.

name: London D Programmers
description: Interested in the D programming language? This group is for anyone wanting to learn, discuss, code or generally enjoy the D programming language.

name: Big Data & High Velocity Analytics - London EC1
description: This group is aimed to assist technologists that are interested in Big Data.  We help organise informal events and meetings in Central London and often have senior technologists and CTO's speak about new technologies emerging within the Big Data space. Please join us for snacks, beer and wine if you are passionate about technology and are looking for ideas and techniques on how to improve ways of finding information within large data sets.

name: import.io users group
description:
This is Extract - powered by import.io. A monthly meetup for workshops and talks related to import.io and big data in London

Join if you want to learn how to gather data with import.io, learn how to use your data or want to meet and talk to other import.io users. Every month we will showcase one of our partners tools from data visualisation to data analytics as well as showing you some neat import.io tricks. 

We also want you to speak. 

Got a cool data project? Come and present!

name: COED:CODE
description: COED:CODE is a warm, fun and encouraging event looking at systems and infrastructure programming. We are crafting a social event designed to give diversity in tech a nudge. The speakers will be mostly women (we're looking at having at least 80% women) and those from other typically under represented backgrounds in technology. Everyone is welcome to attend.

name: London Drupal Pub Meet
description: A chance to meet up with other people in London who use Drupal. This will be a very informal event and all are welcome: developers, designers, hobbyists, business users, people considering Drupal.

name: London Data Governance Meetup
description: Dear DG challengers and pioneers, do you think that data governance matters but still haven't found the answer to where to begin your DG journey? Give our workshop a try and get inspiration from our years of experience in this area. We`ll present our biased view, we`ll be informal, we might even be incorrect and a bit controversial BUT we`ll try not to be boring and we will focus on the important stuff. I promise we'll be frank and we will show you how to get your DG initiative off the ground.

name: London New Relic User Group
description:
Calling all London New Relic Users! This user group is designed to foster the community and connect you with the resources & peers you need to get the most out of New Relic's software analytics suite.


Some of topics we'll discuss:

- Application Performance Monitoring

- Understanding Apdex

- Custom Dashboards & Alerts

- New Relic Insights / NRQL

- More!


Each event features talks from New Relic users and pros alike, with ample time for food, drinks, networking, and discussion. This is a great opportunity to get to know and learn best practices from other New Relic users in the area.


All New Relic users or those interested are welcome!

name: Unified Log London
description:
Apache Kafka and Amazon Kinesis are more than just message queues — they can serve as a unified log which you can put at the heart of your business, effectively creating a "digital nervous system" which your company's applications and processes can be re-structured around.

This is a group for anyone in London and the South-East who is experimenting with Kafka, Kinesis or associated stream processing frameworks like Samza or Storm. If you have read Jay Kreps’ unified log monograph and want to learn how to put these unified log concepts into action, then this is the meetup for you.

Practical and theoretical talks will show how event streams inside a unified log are an incredibly powerful primitive for building rich event-centric applications, unbundling local transactional silos and creating a single version of truth for a company.

name: UK Social Entrepreneurs
description:
Events for social entrepreneurs to share stories, inspire and sharpen each other on their journeys as social enterprise founders. 


The group will focus on (but is not restricted to) technology start-ups interested in social enterprise models.   


Format for events are still being decided with ideas including themed charity events, mentorship evenings and workshops on social enterprise business models. 


If there is any other idea you would be interested in seeing as an event, feel free to get in touch at: ela@ed-fuse.com

name: BI4BP - Business Intelligence for Business People
description:
The group is going to be closed down. Please check out this group:

http://www.meetup.com/Data-Analytics-Business-Intelligence-London-Group/

name: UK Smalltalk User Group
description: The UK Smalltalk user group is a group of professionals and hobbists who share an interest in the Smalltalk programming languages and related technologies.

name: London Machine Learning Study Group
description: This group is for everyone interested in learning more about Machine Learning. We run lectures on Machine Learning algorithms, techniques, and applications. This group is suitable for beginners – we plan to start with the basics and progress to more complex topics over time.

name: Data Science for Internet of Things Meetup - London
description: Hello, This meetup explores the relationship between Data Science and Internet of Things. In essence, we explore the application of predictive learning algorithms to the IoT datasets. We also include Deep Learning. I teach this subject and happy to share ideas and learn from others. Meetings will be on week days in London.

name: Linuxing In London
description:
Linuxing in London is about celebrating Linux. It's about bringing together vendors, suppliers, enthusiasts and IT professionals, and anyone who's just curious about Linux, its strengths, its capacity, and its wonders.

In our real lives we use Linux without even knowing it. It powers Google, Facebook, Docker and most of the Internet infrastructure.

Without Linux the world would not be as connected as it is, or look as it does.

Linux is astonishing, it is changing every week, there are new products coming out, almost at the speed of light. We want to provide a physical forum where people can come together, talk and be informed.

We shall be holding regular talks from specialists on everything from the Linux kernel, the command line to Linux in Cloud computing, and much more.

All of our events are free to participants. We encourage everyone to talk about and to use open source software.  We are Linux distribution agnostic, we like BSD and all derivatives too!

We are drawing up a schedule for the next few month’s talks.

If you have any ideas, suggestions for venues or sponsorship (someone to pay for the soft drinks and nibbles!) please contact us.

Brian Byrne, April 2016.

name: London Business Analytics Group
description:
The London Business Analytics Group is a community data and analytics interest group.  All meetings are free of charge and open to all.  We started in July 2014.  Previous talks have included  data visualisation, exotic patterns in data, big data in personalised medicine, building data science teams, R and predictive analytics.  

Meetings usually start at 6:30pm.  The talk and Q&A last for one hour maximum and there is some time for drinks, chat and networking afterwards. We meet about once a month on a weekday evening at a central London venue.

name: ClusterHQ London
description: This is the London meetup group for users of ClusterHQ's open-source project for running databases, queues, key-value stores and other stateful services inside Docker containers: Flocker (https://github.com/ClusterHQ/flocker). Even if you've never used Flocker, come hang out and learn more about building distributed systems & running data services inside Docker containers.

name: London React Native Community
description:
Community group for users of React Native. Come to share your ideas, problems and solutions.

We will be announcing our first Meetup within the next couple of weeks.

name: Tech City Drupal Meetup
description: Tech City is home to some of the most innovative and influential organisations and individuals in digital. Many of them use Drupal. From newbie to head of digital, from marketing intern to senior strategist or CEO, everyone is welcome to come along for a chat about everything Drupal.

name: SQL Supper
description:
A monthly meeting of data professionals, with a principal but not exclusive focus on the Microsoft Data Platform, Business Intelligence, and Big Data platforms.

We aim to put on a meeting on the last Tuesday of every month featuring two different sessions, one 30 minutes long and the other 60 minutes long.

We'll try to get the doors open at 18:00 each month, with the first session starting at 18:30. These may vary from event to event, so do check the individual event pages for details.

name: Enterprise UX London
description: Enterprise UX is open to all people involved with research, design, strategy and development of enterprise experiences. We welcome researchers, product managers, designers and developers who feel passionate about user experience and improving the lives of daily tasks of our workforce.

name: Grand Challenge Campaign
description:
You can join us to help develop Grand Challenge competitions throughout the UK, recent examples include www.Coins-GrandChallenge.com

The purpose of the Grand Challenge campaign is to find entrepreneurs who can leverage exponential technologies to help solve humanity's most severe challenges, including quality education for all, eradicating poverty and food shortages, the provision of clean water, security, global health, sustainable energy production and distribution, and the environment. Prizes to date have included attending Singularity University's Graduate Summer Programme, and various Executive Courses based at NASA Research Park, nr Mountain View in California, along with attending Wired conferences. 

Members will be interested in knowing how they can support this initiative, from helping to mentor and judge competitors, to supporting the organisation of regional competitions throughout the UK including London, and even helping raise sponsorship. Recent sponsors include Aviva, American Express/ AMEX,  Isle of Man Government, Hoxton Ventures, slowXchange, Blue Wire Capital, Isle of Man Government, Wired.

We can meet in central London to discuss more, location depends on the level of interest <br>

name: The Connected Supper Club
description:
A supper club for thoughtful people. 

We work with hosts, cooks, venues, and speakers, to curate delightful dining experiences.

We will meet, eat, and (among other things) discuss emerging technologies and their impact on life, the universe, and everything. 

We hope these regular feasts will help connect and inspire thinkers, makers, and doers from all walks of life. 

Illustrations by Patu Tifinger patuart.com

name: Pentaho London Usergroup
description: The Pentaho London Usergroup ( PLUG ) has been reformed, now with support directly from Pentaho. We meet to find out the latest goings on with the Pentaho stack, and also to discuss and learn about related technologies. Learning what other users are doing with the product also becomes a great source of inspiration for all. The Pentaho community in London is also growing rapidly (partly fuelled by the rise in Big Data) so come down and make some new contacts. Our events are deliberately kept technically oriented and are not places where you will be accosted by sales people!

name: Agile Data - London Meetup
description: The talks for this Meetup will be related to anything and everything that's both Agile and about Data Science, Big Data or Data Engineering. Talks will range across methodologies, practices, principles, tools, techniques, professionalism, infrastructure and technology where the focus will be on "how" to do Data Science & Engineering, rather than the specifics of "what" is done in Data Science & Engineering.

name: 40Fires
description:
The 40 Fires Foundation is a forum to develop energy-efficient cars using an open source approach. If you are an engineer, a designer or simply an enthusiast interested in helping to make cleaner cars available to all, we want to hear from you! This Meetup group is part of this effort and we aim to meet regularly initially in London.

Our starting point is the design schematics licensed to us by Riversimple. Riversimple has built a hydrogen fuel cell powered network electric car which was unveiled to the public for the first time in London on 16th June 2009.

name: PhD2StartUp : A community of venturesome PhDs
description: This group is meant for graduate/PhD students in the Golden Triangle area of London, Cambridge, and Oxford who want to use their knowledge in the frontiers of science, technology, and society for starting a scalable, high impact venture. Those who are keen to start-up and those who want to explore are both welcome. If you are in the late stage of the PhD or are holding standby post-doc positions with a start-up idea (or many ideas!) that you think can be translated into scalable venture, this is the community that you should be a part of!

name: Code Crew London
description:
Hackers + Designers + Entrepreneurs = Code Crew!

Passionate about learning how to code, creating beautiful designs or building the prototype for your business idea and tired of doing it alone? Then this is the group for you!

This is the perfect group for people serious about learning how to code through self-study using resources on the web like Code School, Codecademy, Treehouse, P2PU, Coursera, edX, Udacity, programming books, screencasts or whatever else is out there on the internet. We also share a helpful suggested reading on our blog and issue occasional code challenges. If you're just starting out and want to get a head start then check out some cool resources here.

We are a group of software engineers, designers and entrepreneurs that enjoy building cool stuff with code at our collaborative coding/pair programming sessions. We currently have members building with HTML, CSS, Javascript, Ruby, Ruby on Rails, Python, Django, PHP, Objective C and more. So come join us and meet some cool and interesting people while picking up a new skill!

name: London 3D Computer Vision & Sensing
description:
This group is for people who are working on or interested in 3D computer vision software/algorithm development and it's applications. With ever cheaper and available sensors, computers, GPUs, HPC, cloud computing and open source software development it's easier than ever to implement sophisticated 3D vision tasks across a huge range of application domains such as robotics, autonomous vehicles, drones/UAVs, industrial inspection and Earth observation satellites.

This group aims to gather a community of researchers, start-ups, hackers and anyone with an interest in 3D vision developments to show-case their projects, give talks and socialise over drinks.

This is a new group, so if you are interested in giving a talk or demo, have ideas for great speakers, or you would like to sponsor a venue/drinks etc then get in touch!

name: FREE Marketing, Analytics & Digital Skills in London
description:
London's Top Learning Community For Digital Professionals & Enthusiasts 
Meet, learn and share with anyone working in or curious about digital.

- Explore tons of new topics   
- Connect across industries
- Learn skills hands-on

Free workshops in London 
- Digital Marketing
- Data Science & Analytics 
- Product Management  
- UX & Design 
- Web Development
See full list of past workshops

How does this work?
1. All our events are free to attend;
2. Anyone may speak for free;
3. We are entirely volunteer-run and non-profit.

Who runs Outreach Digital?
Pro bono volunteers from firms like Amazon, TripAdvisor, Sony PlayStation, agencies like Havas Media and Saatchi & Saatchi, startups like King.com, import.io and MailJet, and a few students and professors, too.
Read more about us

**Top Job Opportunities in Digital**
If you or your company want to submit your job opportunity or wish to partner with us just write to us at outreachdigital.team@gmail.com.

Our friends at Deloitte, the world's largest professional services firm, are currently looking for:
- Data Scientists with Digital Analytics
- Data Scientists with Statistics / Econometrics / SAS
- Mobile Software Engineers
- Front End Developers (Java Enterprise, or .net)
- Retail Analytics Manager with strong analytical backround
Find out more and apply!

**Charity Programme**
We also help other charities and social enterprises, e.g.
- Growth Hacking a Mental Healthcare foundation (affiliated with Oxford University);
- Cooperation with the London Digital Inclusion Network to help kids aged 8-25 get free digital education, including Oculus Rift Virtual/Augmented Reality, 3D Printing and Digital Music production;
- A Mobile App to solve the 2015 European Refugee Crisis; 
If you are a charitable organization, non-profit or social enterprise, and want to collaborate just write to us at outreachdigital.team@gmail.com

Why speak at our events?
Do a workshop or presentation and you will earn plenty of recognition and exposure + potentially also find new clients, talent or business opportunities! What would you like to talk about? Send your idea to outreachdigital.team@gmail.com
More about our speaker opportunities

Why volunteer with us?
We are one of the fastest growing live communities of digital professionals in the world, and this is only possible thanks to pro bono volunteers with a passion to help others and grow at the same time. Want to have fun with a highly motivated and qualified volunteer team?
Find out how to join our team

Why we do this?
Pro bono for us means making a difference in society by using our skills – primarily web development, digital marketing and analytics. Inspired by the legal profession’s pro bono work tradition, our activities ultimately also give volunteers the opportunity to discover, develop and improve in their own areas of interest and career aspirations.
Read our story

More about us on our website: www.outreachdigital.org
Follow us on twitter.com/outreachdigit/
and for industry tips and career opportunities www.linkedin.com/company/outreach-digital/

IMPORTANT  
All our events are organized by pro bono volunteers during their free-time, after working hours, and we choose venues that offer to host us for free. That is a lot of goodwill and thoughtfulness, but because we are no business nor is this our occupation, we kindly ask that by participating you agree to understand the simplicity and limits of our initiative. Despite our best efforts and achievements to date, we are in no way liable for any risk, damage or disappointment that may result from our activities.
Due to the voluntary nature of our organization, contributors and venues, event dates and details may change with short notice. It is your responsibility to check the date and time before arriving, and to enable automatic group notifications on your Meetup profile settings so you are always notified of any changes:
http://www.meetup.com/account/comm/Digital/
Pictures and video may be taken to promote our activities on Meetup and other online media. If you wish to be censored for any reason, kindly inform the event organizer.

name: Spring of Code
description:
Welcome to the Spring of Code group!

We are a civic engagement community creating digital tools to improve democracy and public services.

    This Civic Tech project is based on the ethics of open data, free software, open source and creative commons. So join up, and shout out what's missing from the online tools already out there or how we can make them work better together.

    We advocate for a user centred-design approach as the only way to design digital products and services that people will actually use.

    Who should join?

    Improving democracy isn't just for Developers, it is everyone's mission. To design digital projects that address the needs of users, we need many skillsets involved to analyse, re-think, design, prototype and develop the whole experience. We need service designers, domain experts, UX/UI Designers etc. to bring the right level of expertise to projects.

    What happens in a meeting?

    People meet people, pitch each other projects, share their war stories, talk about product needs, get essential user feedback

    What happens between meetings?

    People buddy up on projects, hack, design, get creative and update on site their progress.

    Do you have a Code of conduct?

    Yes we follow the excellent 18F Code of Conduct.

    ________________________

    So join fellow SpringofCoders right now and start participating in an active, skilled and friendly community.

name: Vaadin London Group
description: Vaadin is a Java framework for building modern web applications that look great, perform well and make you and your users happy. This group represents the London based meetup for Vaadin, where people can meet and exchange ideas and understanding.

name: London API
description:
The London API Group brings together the city's top Web API developers, Web API designers, Web API companies, and industry experts to participate in monthly discussions.

The London API Group is a user group specifically aimed at developers and software engineers, with a focus on software engineering and Web API standards.

This is the meetup group if you want to discuss:

• Web API design and development best practices

• Scaling Web API platforms

• Using third-party Web APIs in your software

We have a Code of Conduct that everyone should abide by.

name: R-Ladies Coding Club (London)
description:
This brand new meetup is a London women's coding club for newer or aspiring R users, and experienced female R programmers interested in mentoring. We are a community designed to encourage, support and ultimately drive the development of our own R skills, through meetups where members tackle hands-on tutorials and exercises to learn specific functionality or attend relevant external events, building knowledge and experience with each event. Promoting women's access to STEM careers & open source! 

PS this community is a social initiative, and will never involve charges or fees to be a member or to attend events hosted by this meetup!

Meetup topics include: 

• Kickstarting R & RStudio

• Job market for R skills (roles, salaries)

• Data Visualisation

• Machine Learning algorithms

• Maths & Stats

• Text Mining

• Spatial Analytics

• Building Interactive Web Apps

• Building Dynamic Reports & Dashboards

• .....and anything else of interest! :)

name: London Machine Learning Practice Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone who wants to learn to apply ML algorithms in practice and deepen their knowledge of the statistical foundations of data science. We will be working in small workshops, and will try to split our time between learning to implement ML algorithms and going through the most important scientific papers on the subject. This group is not for total beginners - basic knowledge of statistics and linear algebra will be required, as well as some basic coding skills (or a desire to learn them quickly!).

name: XMPP UK Meetup
description: This group has been set up to bring together the XMPP/realtime community in London.

name: Drupal Dinners London
description: Come and join us in having a chat about Drupal over a delicious meal.

name: Epic London Tech Jobs - Boolerang.io Meetup!
description:
Interested in finding an epic tech job in London? As many of you will know, Boolerang.io is a socially-motivated tech platform that connects you - London’s brightest, most ambitious techies - with revolutionary startups and big-name companies looking to hire in the city.

Firms currently hiring on the platform include: Escape the City, Improbable, Busuu, Yieldify, Transferwise, Lyst, Future Platforms, Movidiam, 7Digital, BorrowMyDoggy, Movebubble, Kitmapper, StackHut, FundApps & more! In 2016, we're putting you in the driving seat.

We'll be holding a weekly (or monthly) event for you to meet employers currently on the platform! Stay tuned! This is chance to meet the city's leading and most impressive tech employers - from emerging startups to some of the biggest names in tech!

name: London VoIP User Group (LVUG)
description: A meetup for those interested in VoIP standards such as SIP and WebRTC as well as open source software such as Kamailio, FreeSWITCH, Asterisk and OpenSIPs.

name: Flossie.org
description: Flossie is for women interested in using open source as coders, artists and social innovators. Whether you code, tinker, use FLOSS in your projects, want to explore open alternatives, or just want to change the world, all women are welcome - from expert to novice, or anywhere in between.

name: London Ajax User Group
description:
The London Ajax User Group is London's largest group of Ajax, JavaScript, and HTML5 developers. Started in 2010, the group has events at least once a month to discuss all things interesting in the desktop and mobile web world. Meetups, panels, conferences, and pubs.

We meet the 2nd Tuesday of every month at 18:00 at the Skills Matter office. For the larger events we can accommodate approximately 125 guests. Hosts include Dylan Schiemann (Dojo, SitePen, and Intern), Piotr Zalewa (MooTools, JSFiddle), Mustafa Celik, Andy Richardson, and Joe Lee.

For each meetup, we have two 30-60 minute presentations by invited guests. After each event, we head to a local pub. Software engineers, web developers, and anyone interested in learning more about Ajax, JavaScript, HTML5, and mobile should join.

We also have 1-2 all-day events per year.

See http://londonajax.com/ for videos from all of our past events.

We welcome new speakers, you can propose a talk

name: ShoreditchJS
description: Because other tech meet-ups are too mainstream.

name: Canary Wharf .NET User Group
description:
The CWDNUG is a monthly meetup for .NET developers, with a focus on what's relevant (and what's about to be relevant) to developers in the wharf, on the first Wednesday of every month. Expect to see topics such as:

  • WPF & Silverlight.
  • F# & other alternative languages.
  • High volume systems & complex event processing.
  • Agile tools, methodologies and experiences.
  • Open source systems that you can use (or that need your help!).
  • Upcoming releases from Microsoft (WP7, VS2010, TPL).

This meetup's web page is in the process of being set up, so please bear with us and keep an eye on it for any changes!

No recruiters! This user group is for developers to network with other developers in a relaxed yet highly technical and informative setting.

name: PHP London
description: Meet PHP users, developers and recruiters near you! Come to PHP London to exchange ideas and talk about code, architecture, innovation, and open source in general. Anyone interested in PHP is welcome!

name: eCommerce Alliance - Tech Talks
description:
This is a meetup for thought-leadership, ideas and innovations in retail technology with an emphasis on Demandware, Magento, Hybris, WCS and Spree.

The place for sharing experiences, war stories and ideas as well as best-in-class and Open Source solutions, connected but decoupled systems and the challenges of people, process and technology capabilities.

• How to replatform with speed

• Creating a Multichannel architecture

• Taking back control and ownership from SIs

• Flexibility to adapt, innovate and scale

This is the group for you in you are a CTO, CIO, CMO, Director of eCommerce, Marketing, Technology, Applications.

name: UN Influx
description: These events are to explain more details about the UN Influx initiative which 'explores digital opportunities for a better United Nations', primarily through hackathon events.

name: #drivenbydata Meetup
description:
Anyone looking to make better data-driven decisions should come to the #drivenbydata Summit  The Summit is a part of a quarterly series where BIPB ask leading speakers from the Data Science community to share their vision and provoke debate on issues concerning Big Data & Analytics.

Previous speakers have included Dr Robert Barnes; CEO, Turquoise; the London Stock Exchange Group majority owned European Multilateral Trading Facility and Nick Doddy; Global Head of Finance and Foreign Exchange Trade Services & Operationsat Deutsche Bank.

name: Kong/LONDON
description: Come to meet with the Kong developer community in London, hang out with other open source enthusiasts and API fanatics to talk about microservices, APIs and drink good beers.

name: Hive London
description: Welcome to the Hive London meetup. This meetup started with a focus on Apache Hive but extended to everything Big Data and Polyglot Persistence related.

name: London SAP Successfactors Enterprise Apps
description: “This is a group for anyone interested in SAP SuccessFactors Enterprise Extensions. All skills levels are welcome. I started this group because I want to meet other enthusiasts on this topic area. Looking forward to exploring this area of SAP SuccessFactors with everybody.”

name: Automation & Advanced DevOps on AWS - UK Meetup
description: This Meetup is designed primarily for those interested in using AWS and how to secure your production environments on AWS. We are a group of AWS enthusiasts, security and devOps professionals and cloud computing experts who meet up and down the UK. With several high profile data breaches recently, maintaining data security is a top concern for enterprises in the UK. Because security protocols on the cloud are constantly evolving, it is very important to stay up-to-date with the recent changes. At these meetups we will discuss new automation security services, updates to AWS as well as best practices and what is happening in the industry.

name: PyData London Meetup
description: This is a group for users and developers of data analysis tools in Python. The goals are to provide Python enthusiasts a place to share ideas and learn from each other about how best to apply the language and tools to ever-evolving challenges in the vast realm of data management, processing, analytics, and visualization. A goal of PyData groups, events and conferences is to provide a venue for users across all the various domains of data analysis to share their experiences and their techniques, as well as highlight the triumphs and potential pitfalls of using Python for certain kinds of problems. PyData is organized by NumFOCUS.org

name: Turning to Complexity [Beta]
description:
So suddenly, it seems, today’s world became volatile, uncertain, complex, and ambiguous (VUCA), but is this observation based on recent changes or just on change of focus? After all many smart women and men born in the last millennia have grappled with what in the field of social science has been labeled the turn to complexity.

Other fields of science did their turn: in math we have complexity and chaos theory, in physics vast universes with barely countable particles in quantum entanglement defying determinism and leaving space for new theories, philosophy is wondering over dualisms or monoisms, the force of life, and question if it’s not better to return from the lingual to more embodied concepts. In psychology, with its many theories of the mind, seemingly rational thoughts, prove to be born of fast but not so precise automatisms, and memories a construct of constant renarration. The military strategize along VUCA concepts, and business theory is following close.

We all know of globalisation, climate change, migration, shifts in power and maybe of network effects, system theories, process and flow, power laws, the third industrial revolution, and co-evolution of (cyborg) humans and machines. Something is in flux, it does affect us, and in our eyes it is worthwhile to learn more about.

Our intention for this group is to find people who are interested in the “arrival” of awareness of complexity in everyday sensemaking. How does it affect you and me, our family and friends? Do we need to/Could we do something to provide guidance? How does the combination of thoughtful intend and the making of things (“thinkering”) can be used to understand the confusing topic? How could we use physical and digital tools for teaching, learning, experiencing, and navigating in a world of processes and flow?

It would be great to meet a interdisciplinary group of people, bridging silos of profession and approach. Thus artists, designers, coders, scientists, writers, thinkers, tinkerers, or simply curious join us to explore the ways how our daily life looks like looking from the angle of complexity.

We will organise events to share ideas, thoughts, and plan to come up with playful practical investigation methods into the topic.

Potential activities could be: presentations, exhibition visits and reviews, or practical explorations like making topic relevant physical or digital things together. How about the Confused? the app to make decisions, map making, learning tools to viscerally understand probabilities, a chaos pendulum, or discuss how complexity can be expressed visually without falling into visual tropes such as the fractal used above.

Please join and we will then be able to discuss real world meetup and other things to do.

name: Snowplow Analytics London
description: Place for Snowplow users and prospective users to share ideas, use cases, tools and techniques for collecting, analysing and building data-driven products with Snowplow event data

name: HealthTech Women UK
description:
HealthTech Women is a nonprofit organisation empowering girls and women with the expertise and network to revolutionise the future of medical technologies, leading disruptive innovation within the healthcare sector. (Note: We promote women speakers, however our event attendees are always a mix of genders).

www.healthtechwomen.com 

@htw_uk

@Maxi_Macki (Managing Director)

@louisesinclair (Northern Director)

Those running the networking are CO-ORDINATORS, so we would LOVE to hear from the community for any topics/brags/speakers/pitches etc. 

If you would like to get involved in any way big or small with the organisational element of HTW then email Maxine (through Meetup). Social media/blogging/consulting/job searching/event discovery/unsure what you can provide but want to help somewhere - Let us know! The more the merrier (we can add you to the Slack group). The growth of the network depends on more lovely people contributing to it!


Join our interdisciplinary community for access to: 

• Exclusive events featuring leaders in the healthcare industry

• Workshops focused on gaining tangible skills and building expertise

• A global network of influential women and mentors

• Exposure to potential career opportunities. 


Previous HealthTech Women events include:  

• Augmented and Virtual Realities in Healthcare

• The Medical Device Landscape: Today and Tomorrow

• Personalised Medicine

• Gaming Principle in Health

• Big Data in Health

• Personal Health Monitoring

• Showcasing the breadth of HealthTech Sector


This group is of course open to members of all genders!

name: Women Who Code London
description:
If you're interested in being a speaker, host or sponsor, please let the London Leadership Team know or email london@womenwhocode.com.  We're always interested in bringing something new to our coders.

Website - www.womenwhocode.com

Twitter Hashtag - #WWCLondon

Twitter Handle - @WWCLondon

Mission:

Women Who Code is a global nonprofit organization dedicated to inspiring women to excel in technology careers by creating a global, connected community of women in technology. The organization tripled in 2013 and has grown to be one of the largest communities of women engineers in the world.

Empowerment:

Women Who code is a professional community for women in tech. We provide an avenue for women to pursue a career in technology, help them gain new skills and hone existing skills for professional advancement, and foster environments where networking and mentorship are valued.

Key Initiatives:

Free technical study groups

Events featuring influential tech industry experts and investors

Hack events

Career and leadership development

Current and aspiring coders are welcome. 

Bring your laptop and a friend! 

Support Women Who Code:

Donating to Women Who Code, Inc. (#46-4218859) directly impacts our ability to efficiently run this growing organization, helps us produce new programs that will increase our reach, and enables us to expand into new cities around the world ensuring that women and girls everywhere have the opportunity to pursue a career in technology.

Women Who Code (WWCode) is dedicated to providing an empowering experience for everyone who participates in or supports our community, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, ability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or socioeconomic status. Because we value the safety and security of our members and strive to have an inclusive community, we do not tolerate harassment of members or event participants in any form. Our Code of Conduct applies to all events run by Women Who Code, Inc. If you would like to report an incident or contact our leadership team, please submit an incident report form.

WomenWhoCode.com

Twitter | Facebook

name: Microservices Architecture Developer Day
description: Join Red Hat at our next Microservices Architecture Developer Day on Thursday 3rd December at South Bank University. This event provides you with the opportunity to understand best practices as well as what is taking place within middleware products to support Microservices from the developers themselves.

name: PyLadies London
description:
This is a meet up group for anyone involved or interested in the python open-source language. Whether you use it professionally or haven't touched a terminal before, all levels are welcome (INCLUDING COMPLETE BEGINNERS)!

We plan to have informal sessions, workshops and study groups to learn python through small projects, as well as talks.

PyLadies is an international mentorship group with a focus on helping more women and genderqueers become active participants and leaders in the Python open-source community. Our mission is to promote, educate and advance a diverse Python community through outreach, education, conferences, events, and social gatherings. PyLadies also aims to provide a friendly support network for all women and genderqueers, and a bridge to the larger Python world.


Please, read PyLadies Code of Conduct: http://www.pyladies.com/CodeOfConduct/

---------------------

Follow us on Twitter at @PyLadiesLondon : https://twitter.com/pyladieslondon

We are gathering resources on our Github repo: https://github.com/pyladieslondon/resources

name: Kx Community London Meetup
description: This group is for those interested in the kdb+ database and its programming language, q. The idea is to provide an environment for people to meet, chat and present various topics on kdb+ and its industry applications. Everybody from total newbies to q "Gods" are welcome!

name: OpenHFT User's Group
description: OpenHFT promotes doing more with less machines. Whether you need low latency, high throughput, complex models or want to avoid buying more hardware to solve your problems, OpenHFT products achieve more performance from the hardware you have in Java. Come to our sessions to network with developers who like to push the limits of what Java can do for you.

name: GOTO Nights - London, UK
description:
GOTO Nights are designed for people who want to stay up to date with the latest tools, technologies, processes and practices in the software industry.

GOTO Nights are free evening events driven by involvement from both speakers and participants. Come along to learn something new and network with your peers! We will provide you with a first class speaker - all you have to do is show up!!

GOTO Nights provide you with an opportunity to:

• Hear world-class speakers

• Learn about the latest trends

• Reach beyond your current language, platform, or practices

• Increase your technical depth and breadth

• Expand your professional network

• Share your experience and expertise with others

• Connect with the global software community

We cover a vast range of topics on our meetups, and if you have a topic you are keen to learn more about, please let us know and we'll try to organise a talk.

name: Drupal London Community
description:
The Drupal London community organises regular general Drupal events, events focusing on specific sectors or user cases, and takes part in various trade shows.

The Drupal Drop In user group events have been held regularly since 2006 and are a great place to watch presentations on new modules and techniques, put your questions to the experts, and network with the rest of the community.

Drupal Focus events are half day conferences with presentations, discussions, and networking about specific sectors such as Education, Publishing, Government or topics such as Media Handling, Theming, and Maintenance.

name: London Perl Mongers
description:
Founded in 1998, the London Perl Mongers has regular social, technical meetings and hackdays about the Perl programming language and related topics. The technical meetings are a chance to find out what has been going on in the Perl community, what techniques people are using and how Perl integrates with other software.

See our website for more information about our activities.

Subscribe to the london-pm-announce list for up-to-date information about London PM events. Join the london.pm list for general chat. We also strive to keep the calendar (gcal) up-to-date.

name: Mendix United Kingdom
description: This is a group for Mendix developers and anyone interested in becoming a Mendix developer, in the United Kingdom. All skill levels are welcome, and we encourage you to invite your friends and colleagues to our growing community of business and IT professionals. We're looking forward to seeing you at our next meetup!

name: Applied Deep Learning Meetup
description: This group is for mathematicians, artificial intelligence specialists and deep learning specialist who want to exchange experience with different models, algorithms and tools. We are from industry and academia. We use tools such as Caffe, Theano or Torch. We use algorithms such as Convolutional Deep Neuronal Networks, Deep Belive Networks, Deep Kernel Machines, Stacked (Denoising) Auto-Encoders and Deep Boltzmann Machines. Applied fields include speech recognition, robotics, natural language processing, image and video recognition and pattern recognition in sensor data. We do not accept people without knowledge of AI. Sorry recruiters and agencies ;-)

name: Geek Girls Carrots UK
description:
