Geek Girls Carrots is a community of women who love new technologies. It is a community for us
to participate and act on our passions. Among us there are programmers, graphic designers, project managers, planners, system architects, developers, IT managers, computer science students, analysts, social media specialists, girls with startup ideas and many more. Sometimes, we are joined by journalists who want inspiration for articles about local talent and new technologies.
The mission of our community is to promote women in IT and help to educate them and inspire their pursuits. We also want to motivate women to run their own projects and establish new technology related companies.
At our meetings we discuss topics related to the new technologies and careers in the field. We have no theme, focusing primarily on the selection of insuring and interesting speakers.
Currently Geek Girls Carrots operated in 14 cities in Poland, 1 in Germany, 1 in the USA  2 in Luxembourg and 1 in London.

name: Silicon Abbey
description: Silicon Abbey is an initiative based in St Albans. Our mission is to ensure that Hertfordshire has a digital future. We facilitate networking between interesting and inspiring people, we get involved in tech education and we want to encourage and mentor an innovative industry in Hertfordshire.

name: Apache Kafka London
description:
This group is addressed to London Apache Kafka users. We welcome software engineers, systems architects, data scientists, software developers and anyone interested in Apache Kafka. This group is also addressed to people interested in advanced system architecture, real time event streaming and the Internet of Things.

Join this group if you would like to learn more about Apache Kafka and the technologies related. Also join if you'd like to share your current project experiences, hear about real life use cases, learn about best practices, how to tune your Kafka deployments and how to develop software that uses it.

We'll organise monthly events where community members will talk about their experiences or about specific technical aspects. Talks will be followed by networking.

We hope these talks and networking events will make Apache Kafka London the place were the fast growing Kafka users community in London gets to know each other.

name: Linked Data London
description: London Meetup for all interested in the technologies and developments around linking data, semantic, graph and open data. Experts, users, enthusiasts and newbies are all welcome.

name: MDN : Mozilla Developer Network
description:
Wednesday Docs are monthly meetings in London and Paris, where we get together and work on writing or translating docs on MDN. You are welcome to come and work on whatever interest you!

Bring your laptop and start contributing to MDN :) If you can't come, join us on the #mdn channel on IRC (irc.mozilla.org) and say hi!

name: DevOps in the 'ditch
description:
Here at 7digital we're getting all excited about DevOps. We like to think we've always had the open and collaborative culture that is intrinsic to the DevOps approach, and lately we've been spending quite a lot of time experimenting with various ways of working, team organisation, and technical tools.

The DevOps community is a lively place, and we thought it'd be great to host a regular event where we could hear a short presentation and then have a good chat about whatever comes up over some drinks and snacks.

We're planning on running DevOps in the Ditch in alternate months to our sister event, Devs in the Ditch (meetup.com/devs-in-the-ditch).

name: Londata
description:
About Londata:

We created Londata to provide a space where people interested in the commercial opportunities presented by data can come together, listen to a great speaker or two and share war stories. Our aim is to make our attendees and their companies even more successful.

Check out the 60s second digest from Londata III with Moshi Monsters below...

 

 

If you want to follow us @londataevent the hash tag is #londataevent

name: Applied Artificial Intelligence London
description: Our mission is to showcase AI by bringing together leading corporates and cutting-edge startups to present their advancements, challenges and direction with real life AI applications. The talks strike a balance between highly technical and business overviews; covering all industries from fraud detection and product recommendation to computer vision and natural language processing. If you are technically minded and have an interest in AI and Machine Learning please join us at our next meetup.

name: London Tech Meetup
description:
Interested in learning more about technology and innovation ,we offer an unique opportunity to learn more directly from the founders and developers .

Once a month we give UK technology companies an opportunity to take the stage and introduce their innovative solution and products to our members .

be the first to hear about a new app ,website ,cool gadget ,software or even a solution…its making people's life easier, Join most innovative technologists for a live demos from companies developing new technology in London.

We re looking to host demo of different innovative solutions and new Ideas .

Our main aim to encourage innovative startups and individuals by giving them more exposure and the opportunity to meet potential investors to develop and succeed their projects .

Come to join us to network and meet talented and innovative technologites . 

our events are accessible to everyone.

name: Challenge Big Data, Hosted by Pentaho
description: Welcome to the Challenge Big Data Meet-up, hosted by Pentaho. This group will give you chance to find out about events that are focused on discussing the current trends and challenges faced by businesses entering the Big Data world.

name: Talker Club
description: We meet in the city and talk subject we like in language we learn.

name: Smart Earth Network
description:
The pressures facing species and ecosystems across the planet demand a radical change in conservation solutions.

Smart Earth Network is a new social enterprise whose aim is to create a framework within which conservationists, technologists and entrepreneurs can collaborate, fund and develop solutions for conservation.

The focus is on two areas:

The enhancement of systems for the monitoring, evaluation, decision-making and action related to conservation biodiversity.

The proving of claims made by environmentally accredited products and services.

This Meetup is one of the activities of the Smart Earth Network, providing a forum for conservationists and technologists to share experiences and ideas and discuss how best to develop the network.

Get involved and please signup as member of our network!

name: Data! Data! Data!
description:
“Data!data!data!" he cried impatiently. "I can't make bricks without clay.” - Arthur Conan Doyle.

Key movers and shakers of the datasphere coming together to discuss news, ideas and what's hot in the world of data. Enjoy!

name: Communication Hack
description: This group is for anyone interested in bringing advanced communication skills to collaborative projects.  Ideal for startups, app developers, project managers, and anyone who is interested in their communication being clear, effective and leading to better results.

name: Box User Group - EMEA
description: This is a group for anyone interested in cloud technology, collaborating, build applications, manages content or mobile devices, is an Admin to ERP/ ECM/ CRM, innovation etc. If you can bring your vision to Box and join our discussions or hackathons, we invite you to join us. All skills levels are welcome! Since the technologies are changing fast and should be simplified, we'd love to share and hear what this SAAS and PAAS model is worth to the current and future enterprise environment. Main focus is to keep these 4 pillars in place: - Collaboration - Security - Mobility - Platform - open API

name: Big Data Innovation World Meetup Tour
description:
This is a group for those interested in collaborating and thought sharing within the fields of big data and analytics. We aim to create a global community to lead the Big Data revolution.

All skill levels are welcome.

With a vast amount of data now available, understanding and managing this data is crucial. Meetups will feature in-depth discussions, war stories and sharing best practices. The first two hours will consist of short presentations and discussions followed by an hour of drinks and networking.

If you'd like to see any sessions in particular or present something, please let me know.

The first session will be taking place 23rd January 5pm - Venue TBC (London EC)

name: Pluralsight: Meet the Authors [UK]
description: Meet the Authors is a Meetup with a difference. A User Group with a multi-discipline culture, where all sessions are presented by Pluralsight authors - some of the most knowledgeable teachers and practitioners in the industry. Come along to hear great topics presented by experts, and have your questions answered!

name: The Enterprise Hackers Social Club London
description:
We’re calling this The Enterprise Hackers Social Club because it’s dedicated to the people making it happen at big companies, the heroes of IT, the rebels of software architecture :) If you're a developer and care about APIs, scalability, distributed systems, identity management, security, or just build really cool stuff... let's drink!

The Enterprise Hackers Social Club no longer has an organiser, so I've stepped in temporarily to propose that we merge this group with a Meetup that I already run called the London Enterprise Tech Meetup.

I'll keep this group active until the end of the year, when I'll also step down - anyone else is welcome to step in please let me know and I'll transition over.

name: London Applied Artificial Intelligence Meetup
description: We're a group of founders, AI practitioners, hackers, investors and senior industry experts looking to find and develop interesting applications for AI. We meet informally over dinner in VC / startup boardroom in London, hear some very short talks from sector experts on opportunists and brainstorm ways of potentially building an AI based business around them. If the potential of AI gets you excited and you fit in to any of the categories above come and say hi! We started this group because the conference scene and founder meetup groups are an incredibly inefficient way of finding like minded people, we'd rather just say what we're looking to do and see who else has the same drive to make it happen.

name: West London Hack Night
description:
Join us for a monthly evening of programming challenges to stretch and inspire you.

We provide the problems and place that welcomes all languages & all skill levels; you bring an eager mind and a geeky heart. Together, we hack and learn. And teach.


Note for non-programmers: If you're interested, you're very welcome to join us. Just bear in mind this isn't hacking in the Television sense - we won't be breaking into anything. This is hacking in the "do something fun with computers" sense.

name: The London Big-O Meetup
description:
There is more to the world than “functional cloud based self learning big data analytic enterprise visualisation dashboards”.

The only meetup focusing on data structures and algorithms, regardless of programming language or application domain.

No marketing speak. No handwaving.

Its easy to loose track of these fundamentals in day to day jobs and given how important they are for code quality and performance its worth giving them some dedicated time. Even if its just to prepare for you next job interview.

Examples of talks:

  • The Fast Fourier Transform, more useful than you think
  • Training deep neural networks: complexity analysis
  • The pumping lemma: Why should you care?
  • The multi-objective knapsack problem: strategies and applications
  • Leader election for collaborative drones
  • Variational inference in Bayesian Networks
  • Genetic Algorithms in Formula 1 design
  • ...

More examples and details here.

We have a healthy attendance with a good technical crowd. If you'd like to speak about your favourite data structure or algorithm, or if you just have a request for a talk, send an e-mail to the list or get in touch with the organiser.

Twitter account: @bigoldn
Hashtag: #bigoldn

name: London Open Data Missions
description:
Calling all open data and transparency activists to join us every last Wednesday of the month for liberating data and lightening talks. Whether you can write a few lines of code to write a bot, or a journalist who is interested in covering stories on transparency, or a campaigner who champions an open and free world - come along to meet like-minded people and use open data to change the world.

If you are an NGO who would like to suggest a mission for these meetups - do get in touch at hera@opencorporates.com

Powered by missions.opencorporates.com // OpenCorporates

name: Python and Django Coding Session
description:
This is a biweekly meetup where we get together and work on Python/Django projects. Bring your own projects, laptop, and any issues you've been dealing with. We'll provide a collaborative coding environment, help each other become better developers and make progress on what we're working on. Developers of all levels are welcome!

Location: Conversocial (Second Floor), Epworth House, 25 City Road, EC1Y1AA

name: WordPress User Group - Greenwich (WUGG)
description:
A local group where WordPress users commune and share knowledge about WordPress and related activities such as blogging, social media, image editing, and general web skills.

We strive to cater for all levels. More experienced users and industry professionals give presentations with opportunities for Q&A, at other meetups users can present their challenges and receive support from the group and an opportunity to discuss emerging methods and techniques.

name: London Machine Learning Meetup
description: We're a group of like-minded developers and scientists interested in Machine Learning, Probabilistic Graphical Models and Natural Language Processing. In this meetup, we hope to bring together machine learning practitioners to listen to each other's work alongside running a study group focused on the Stanford courses (ml-class.org, pgm-class.org and nlp-class.org).

name: London Selenium Meetup Group
description:
• London Selenium Meetup [#LDNSE]
The London Selenium Meetup [#LDNSE] is an open forum where Selenium users of all skill levels can come to communicate, learn, network, or just have a good time.Our focus is in Selenium and topics extend through related areas of interest, such as Agile testing, Test-Driven Development, Behaviour Driven Development, Continuous Integration, Continuous Deployment, building maintainable automated test scripts and much more.
• Topics Covered 
We are Selenium users but not limited to 'Selenium' only. We can talk about any tool which uses WebDriver JSON wire protocol. This can include Selenium integrated with following tools Cucumber, Appium, Behat, PhantomJS, Jenkins & other CI tools, Continuous Delivery,  SpecFlow, Mobile,Test Automation with Selenium, Cloud Testing Frameworks etc etc
• Submitting Talk
You can submit talk for the future Selenium Meetup by filling 'Talk Submission' form. 
• Sponsoring Meetup events 
You can sponsor event if you want to show how you use to the community. Sponsoring means providing space and cost of refreshments. Your company will be added  in the list of the sponsors on meetup page with logo. Please contact organizer if you wish to sponsor upcoming Selenium events. 
• Selenium London on Social Media
Official hashtag is #LDNSE Twitter:  @SeleniumLondon FaceBook : seleniumlondon Youtube : Channel : seleniumlondon SpeakerDeck: Follow presentation 'seleniumlondon'

name: London - Get More From Data
description: This group is aimed at informing people about latest tools and techniques with Analytics along with a chance to network with others in the industry. Whether it's Visualisation, Segmentation, Big Data or any other related area, these events will be a chance to further your knowledge and meet those with similar interests.

name: Art Hackathon
description: Members of the London Hackspace and staff from Ravensbourne are organizing an Art Hackathon on the 16th and 17th of May 2015. Fifty artists-hackers and hacker-artists will get together over a weekend in one big, state-of-the-art space to demonstrate the expressive potential of new technology and the power of radical collaboration in art by setting up an art exhibit from scratch. Invited guest artists kick-start the event by showing their work and food, fast internet link, 3D printers, hardware for quick prototyping and help by skilled volunteers will be provided. For more details as well as to register, visit: http://arthackathon.co.uk

name: Cognitive Computing
description:
Welcome to the third era of computing. Computer-based information processing  is now a practical reality that is ubiquitous and pervasive in so many things that we do today. Nevertheless the power of computing largely remains implicit, unappreciated and even misunderstood to the most.

We are at the dawn of Cognitive Computing. Where the power of information processing meets highly adaptive cognitive algorithms and vast data sets and sensor inputs about all aspects of our lives. The destiny is limited by our capacity to imagine and harness this vast potential underneath man-machine-data interaction.

In this meet up, we will discuss about the trends in computing; around predictive analytics, machine learning techniques that utilizes large and disparate data sets and about emerging platforms that support all these, for example, IBM Bluemix. And we will roll up our sleeves and start working on some practical examples and contribute to the community.

name: GO & AWS Croydon User Group
description: AWS and Go are two exciting technologies and the idea of this group is to teach, learn and exchange know-how and be part of the Croydon tech revolution. with Go you can build good software and AWS made it so easy to deploy the good GO (or any other) software.

name: London Computer Security Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in Security, Architecture, Cloud building and Big Data, etc. All skills levels are welcome. I started this group because to meet other enthusiasts. Looking forward to exploring this topic with everybody.

name: QuruLabs - Somerset House (Linux and Open source)
description:
Welcome to QuruLabs, an opportunity for IT professionals to meet and discuss how to use Linux and open-source based products to solve today's business IT challenges. At each monthly meet-up we will focus on a specific topic.

 Through a combination of a demonstration and discussion, our aim is to provide practical demos and an exchange of views, ideas and experiences. 

In the ethos of open source, we are looking to meet new people and collaborate about solving key IT challenges using open source solutions.

We also invite key open source community members to our meetups, so that they can share what they're working on.

name: Data Scientist
description:
Data Scientist Meetup is for professionals, entrepreneurs, students and data geeks involved in data mining, business intelligence, data visualisations and predictive analytics.

Our Meetups will be taking place on a monthly basis starting from Thursday, 8th of October 2015 and then every first Thursday of a month. There will be a small participation fee to confirm the RSVPs and cover organisational basics (e.g. room hire, beer, pizza, speakers etc.).

name: London Dato users
description: This group is for developers and data scientists in London using Dato tools like GraphLab Create, as well as anyone interested in applied machine learning. Join us.

name: Artificial Intelligence in the Enterprise
description: This is a group for anyone interested in Artificial Intelligence, how it can be used in the enterprise and what benefits it can bring. This group was started to meet others with an interest in AI technology and to share different experiences

name: emagine - Business & IT experts
description: A group of like-minded Business & IT experts interested networking, meeting other specialists in the market and discussing all topics related to Financial Services and technologies such as Hadoop, Spark, Cassandra, MongoDB, Scala, Python, Qlikview, Spotfire and Tableau.

name: Technology & Innovation for Retail, Finance & Digital
description:
Need inspiration from a Thought Leader, want to hear about the latest Technologies or just want to network with like-minded techies, marketeers and business leaders in Retail, Finance and Digital, then this is the place to meet, share and collaborate. 

With regular events, the aim is to bring the best in technology for enterprise, web and mobile applications for Finance and Retail with great speakers and topics as well as beer/wine and food!

name: Couchbase London
description:
What is Couchbase?

Couchbase is the company behind Couchbase open source project, a vibrant community of developers and users of Couchbase document-oriented database technology. 

Couchbase Server is a packaged version of Couchbase technology that’s available in Community and Enterprise Editions. Couchbase is known for easy scalability, consistent high performance, 24x365 availability, and a flexible data model. 

Companies like AOL, Cisco, Concur, LinkedIn, Orbitz, Salesforce.com, Shuffle Master, Zynga and hundreds of others around the world use Couchbase Server for their interactive web and mobile applications.

Sign up to our Couchbase Developer Newsletter

name: London Drupal Learning Meetup
description:
We think Drupal is an awesome content management and development framework (see www.drupal.org)

The Learning Drupal Meetup is for people who are interested in sharing experience and knowledge about all things Drupal. It's a great opportunity for some informal Drupal learning and for exchanging ideas of better ways to learn Drupal concepts and solutions.

The meetup is free, organised by volunteers and open to anyone who is interested in learning more about Drupal in an informal, collaborative way. Come prepared to meet friendly fellow Drupalers and to share your knowledge - whether you are an experienced Drupal users or a newbie.

name: London Salesforce Admins
description: This is a group for those people who spend their days working behind the scenes of the Salesforce setup menu to configure, customise and extend the functionality of Salesforce business applications. Whether you are a member of an in-house team or employed as an external consultant, we all have something in common. That is, keeping up to date with a continually evolving platform and the need to learn and share our experiences of best practice. Those who are not new to the world of Salesforce already know, understand, and often preach WHY Salesforce cloud benefits the businesses which use it. The aim of this group is to bring people together to talk HOW to get the job done and deliver those benefits. The word used to identify people who carry out these tasks on the Salesforce platform is "admin", but as we all know there are many many different roles which sit behind the label. This group is a place for us all to gather, whether the majority of our time is spent on end-user support, or business analysis, or responding to business change that needs additional validation and workflows to be created, or integrating with different platforms using 3rd party tools, the list goes on and on. There is already a strong Salesforce community centred around London, this group aims to serve the needs of Salesforce admins in particular by providing a place to meet face-to-face and build new relationships, share personal experiences and see hands-on examples of Salesforce configuration techniques using all the features. The group will welcome members who are new to the world of Salesforce, or who may be considering in becoming a Salesforce admin in the future. We're going to need more people in order to build all these business applications in the cloud! Welcome #awesomeadmin!

name: Find a Tech Job In London
description:
Techie looking for a job? Company that hires Techies?

We make it easy to meet each other, and see if if it's worth proceeding to a full interview, in a low stress and enjoyable evening event.

Repeat attending companies include Sky, Which?, TicketMaster, KPMG, GameSys and many lesser known SMEs and startups.

Developers, designers, product managers, project managers, system administrators, testers, analysts - you're all welcome.

name: AngularJS London
description:
Welcome to the Angular London community.

AngularJS London is the largest Angular meetup in Europe. We hold meetups every month in various locations around London. What to give a talk? Submit your ideas here goo.gl/qHICoi

If you would like to connect to the community you can join our Slack channel. To get an invite go to angularjs-london.herokuapp.com

AngularConnect - the official European Angular Conference is coming back to London this year. Visit angularconnect.com to find out more.

name: London Alfresco Meetup Group
description: This group is aimed at everyone involved with Alfresco in and around London, whatever the level of expertise. We plan to arrange meetups in all aspects of Alfresco - 'how to' sessions, new feature presentations, social meetups - and anything else that you think you'd like to see! This group is open to developers and users of Alfresco.

name: DevOps Exchange - London
description:
We are now the WORLDS largest DevOps meetup - if you care about DevOps this is the meetup to join! :)

If you're a DevOps or Operations person running an online/cloud service in London, this group is for you! A chance to exchange some of the latest ideas and technologies for running online services through 2-3 short presentations by invited speakers, and a chance to chat it after over drinks/snacks with new friends. 

We started this event as as we love DevOps and have seen an insatiable demand for more knowledge about it from teams running online/cloud services in London. We now run it monthly and have become London's largest DevOps Meetup attracting the best speakers and crowd interested in sharing the best ideas around DevOps with the community.

name: London OpenStack Meetup
description: This group is for anyone interested in cloud technology, especially Openstack. If you are interested or involved in providing scalable computing resources, be they virtualised, cloud, 'on demand' or grid then you'll find something here.

name: DevWax - standup on the wave
description: Technology is an adventure. Board meetings should involve paddling out and standups should have wipe outs. Join us for a few days of talking tech, coding, building product and surfing. Bring a laptop, a tent, a wetsuit and positivity. There may also be climbing, yoga, beer and a bbq.

name: London Data Science #ODSC
description:
#ODSC brings together the open source and data science communities with the goal of helping its members learn, connect and grow.

The focus of this Meetup group is to allow #ODSC to work with Meetup groups, non-profits, and other organizations to present informative lectures, workshops, code sprints and networking events to help grow the use of open source languages and tools within the data science and data-centric community. As such, our specific goals are:


1. Build a collaborative group to work with other Meetup groups, non-profits, and other organizations.

2. Promote the use of open source languages and tools amongst data scientists and others.

3. Host educational workshops.

4. Spread awareness of new open source languages and tools that can be used in data science.

5. Contribute back to the open source community.



Who is this meetup for?

• Data engineers, analysts, scientists, and other practitioners

• R, Python and other software engineers who work with data or want to learn

• Data visualization developers and designers

• Non-technical team leads, executives, and other decision makers from data centric startups and large companies looking to utilize open source tools


How can you get involved?

• Attend events, network and precipitate!

• Give a talk or workshop that meets our goals

• Volunteer to help the group (social media, website, blogging)

• Provide us with a venue

• Sponsor food and drinks

name: Marklogic Financial Services Community
description: The aim of or the Marklogic Financial Services Developer Community is to join people together within the Financial Services Community who have experience of Marklogic or just want to find out more!  We'll aim to meet up for a beer and nibbles regularly so we share our experiences and get to know each other!

name: Robotics[London]
description:
This is a group for enthusiasts of robotics technology!

We think robotics and the related areas of AI, machine learning and computer vision have the potential to transform and improve quality of life and help a number of vital industries. London is a leading centre for robotics research and lots of new and exciting startups are appearing. 

This is a group for people from any background or discipline wanting to learn about the latest developments and discover new ways to apply robotics technology to help solve problems.

Our meetups will be informal and social. There'll be demos / showcases of robotics in action and an opportunity to meet fellow robotics enthusiasts.

This group was created by the team behind FlyWave, a London based startup that's creating a data analysis platform for drone operators.

name: South London Tech Meetups
description: We’re an informal platform for tech South of the river. Our aim is to bring together the many tech companies and people in Lambeth and South London, primarily by organising informal meetups and great speaker events.

name: London CoffeeScript Users' Group
description: This is a group for all software developers who are currently using, or who want to become more involved with, CoffeeScript.

name: London Legal Hackers
description: Hackers, this is a call to Action! A call to Arms. This is an unprecedented year documenting our loss of Privacy. Never before have we needed to stand up and team up to do something about it. The Data Privacy Legal Hackers is all about doing something about it. This group is for everyone who caress. Show your support and join the group.

name: DataKind UK
description: Calling all data do-gooders: DataKind UK is a meetup for the United Kingdom chapter of DataKind, a community of data scientists and non-profits working together to better collect, analyze, and visualize data in the service of humanity. DataKind encourages local meetups to share ideas, collaborate across communities, discuss new tools and practices, and help bring about a better world through data for social causes. Come hang out with other conscientious dataists and tech-savvy social innovators doing great things for the world here in the UK. We host regular drinkups, speaker series, and social events. Find out more about us at http://www.datakind.org.uk If you're organizing a DataKind meetup in your city, drop a line to contact@datakind.org.uk and let us know!

name: GDG Cloud London
description:
Google Cloud Platform London is a non-profit community of cloud developers who are interested in learning and sharing their use cases of GCP.
Our events are open to newbies, developers, managers and organisations who are interested in Google Cloud Platform or use them as part of their projects.

Build, Store, Analyze using Google Cloud Platform.

name: Ruby Hacknight - London
description:
An open, relaxed meetup for all levels of web developers to come and talk shop, share knowledge, collaborate and hack on all manner of web and mobile projects.

We're focused on a creating a welcoming and inclusive community of developers at all skill levels. The only requirement is a healthy intrigue of web or mobile programming and the desire to dive right into a hack. The format is straight-forward and involves consuming free pizza and drinks provided by Yammer whilst discussing and hacking on any project you desire. We encourage members to use the meetup discussion board to post their current projects and to coordinate with fellow developers. If you don't have a current project, don't worry! Attending the meetup is a great way to see what others are working on and to find inspiration for your own endeavours.

We take your safety very seriously. Before attending, please be sure to read our Anti-Harassment Policy.

name: Internet of Things Innovators UK
description: Everyone who has a firm interest in Internet of Things technology. This meetup is about all things device and server-stack for IoT.

name: MEAN Stack
description:
This group is for anyone interested in learning more about the MEAN Stack (MongoDB, ExpressJS, AngularJS and Node.js) which is the latest stack around allowing developers to do rapid application development and application scaffolding.

Join us if you're interested in this new development stack or if you're simply interested in full stack web development, especially JavaScript as a programming language.

All skill levels are welcome as we do have presentations that are for absolute beginners and we also bring in experts to deliver in detail presentations about particular technologies.

name: London AI
description:
London's meetup for: Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Cognitive, Intelligence Augmented, Natural Language Processing, Robotics, Neural Networks, Machine Ethics, Human Machine Symbiosis...lets call it AI. 

London AI is a community that brings startups, corporates and academics in the AI sphere together to understand how the technology is being used today, and what is coming soon. While some of our talks will take a technical deep dive, the forum is open to all those with a strong interest in the next era of human-machine symbiosis. 

London.AI is co-founded and run by Alex Flamant and John Henderson. Alex has a strong interest in early stage machine learning and NLP projects, with a focus on BlueChip-Startup collaborations. When he is not working on London.AI, Alex is the Watson Ecosystem’s BD Manager for EMEA, bringing cognitive technology to the local ecosystem. John is an investor in early stage companies at White Star Capital where he has a particular focus on machine intelligence.  His interest in the space stems back to his previous role as COO of Summly, an NLP company which was acquired by Yahoo in May 2013.  John has also held roles at Facebook and The Boston Consulting Group. 

Check out our page more information: http://www.london.ai

name: West Is Best Tech Meetups
description: West London Community tech meetups to discuss Innovation, Technology, Software Development Trends, Creating Business Value

name: Data Science & Business Analytics London Meetup
description: This is dedicated to explore the user cases, best practices for data science in business. Follow #DataScience4Biz

name: AppDynamics London User Group
description: The London AppDynamics user group is an interactive group gathering for all AppDynamics users in London to discuss trends in APM technology and AppDynamics best practices. The London AppDynamics User Group is technical but also people-oriented. It is a valuable opportunity to exchange ideas and learn from other users about AppDynamics and Application Performance Management in general.

name: London Internet Startups
description:
Chapter of Global Internet Startups Meetup group, London Internet Startups (LIS) was founded in July 2015 and it is one of the fastest growing startup communities in the United Kingdom.

Our events empower entrepreneurs by connecting people and creating opportunities for companies to develop new businesses, meet customers, launch new products, promote their brands and expand their markets.

This group strives to help: Entrepreneurs, Students, Techies, Startups, Investors, Mentors and Advisors.

This group will: Host great events, get you involve, connect people, help you take action.

Join, Participate and Enjoy! ☺

Home to some of Europe's hottest startups, London is an emerging force in the world of innovation. The purpose of this group is to bring together members of the local and international community to support and foster the growth of a thriving startup hub. Let's see how we can collaborate now and in the future to create, sustain and enable new and greater startups. 

We are glad to have you on board and look forward to meeting you at one of our frequent events.

Sincerely, 

Jeff Robinson & the LIS Team

P.S. You can find all our Meetups here: Global Internet Startups. Check us out when you're traveling or if you ever move abroad!

name: DataSift Developer Meetup London
description:
We've created this meetup for existing DataSift developers and for anyone looking to learn more about working with social and human data. 

Come along to learn about our platform, pick up new ideas and use cases for data, and meet other developers / data scientists / analysts working in the same space.

We'll provide the speakers, drinks and snack - you just need to come along and join in!

name: The London entrepreneurial Meetup group
description: SUCCESS! Join the London Entrepreneurial Meetup Group, Welcome happy startups, investors, entrepreneurs, students, tech lovers !!!

name: Drupal West London
description:
At our monthly Drupal meetups we get together to talk, share knowledge and exchange ideas. Introductions, getting to know how we're using Drupal and supporting eachother to increase our skills.

Also seeing what people's needs are and planning future events to fit in with those needs along with some social events of course!

General Drupal Q&A for anyone attending (beginner through to advanced)

Bringing our problems (and possibly laptops too!) to the table and see if we can come up with solutions together

Spreading awareness of any upcoming events of interest and mentioning interesting opportunities

Update on progress of the group aims and any other general business

The event is hosted by Imagine Creativity

name: The future of Artificial Intelligence
description: Artificial Intelligence (AI) is the form of intelligence that arises from machines, perceiving their environment and taking actions to maximize their chance of success for a given task. We live in a period where computer power is escalating quickly and where recent discoveries are bringing this power to the general public, often arising controversy. In this ecosystem, academia and industry define together a new paradigm to innovate and benefit humanity as a whole. Don't miss the opportunity to learn about AI in London, together with Imperial College London Innovation Forum (ICLIF).

name: Storm - London User Group
description:
Are you interested in Twitter's open source distributed realtime computation framework "Storm" & based in London? Then this meetup is for you.

We get together to share use cases, experiences and tips on how to use this framework.

"Storm is a distributed realtime computation system. Similar to how Hadoop provides a set of general primitives for doing batch processing, Storm provides a set of general primitives for doing realtime computation." Project GitHub

 

Group photo courtesy of Paul Bica

name: The Business of IoT
description:
The Business of IoT

A meetup group looking at the business models, technology platforms and data that are behind the IoT.

Our focus is the business side of IoT: We want bring together established and up-and-coming players in the commercial IoT, to reflect and discuss what needs to happen to leverage the huge potential of connected devices across and build bridges into the often closed ecosystems of different vendors.

Our core themes are

• business models supported by IoT 

• bringing it all together, how to connect data silos, open up and share your data in the ecosystem

• the broader world and how to bring location and physical context together

• devices at scale, meshed networks, NFC, Thread and other emerging standards

• scalable platforms and models - the backend of IoT, how do you deal will billions of events a day, support, customer service

• supporting technologies - what technologies can support business at this scale

name: London Netezza Meetup
description: This Meetup is for any existing PureData for Analytics (aka Netezza) customers who want to swap hints, tips, stories, questions, or experiences. It's also for anybody interested in learning more about how to perform complex statistical or geographical analysis on terabytes of data (e.g. customer, transaction, clickstream, social, etc.) in seconds flat, perhaps as part of a Big Data integration strategy. We'll also try and get someone from IBM along to update us on the latest developments in the Information Management space.

name: London RethinkDB Meetup
description: This is a group where people get together to talk about RethinkDB. Being a relatively new database the aim of this group is to share stories of using RethinkDB. We plan to have events running every 6-8 weeks.

name: Object Storage & Craft Beer - London
description: This is a group for Storage & Cloud architects that are interested in keeping up to date with technology innovation & drinking Craft Beers, Ciders & Gins. London is the centre for so much innovation in technology, as well as brewing & distilling that I thought we should combine the two. Keeping up to date with tech while drinking craft beer, what's not to like?

name: Apache Flink London Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone who wants to learn about or share what they know about Apache Flink. We are excited about its potential, and we want to find other people who are interested. Apache Flink is a 'streaming first' data processing engine - which is a lot cooler than it sounds. See here for more: https://flink.apache.org/

name: London Apache Drill
description: Dedicated to learning more about the application of Apache Drill in Big Data environments

name: JUST EAT London Developer Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in software development in general. We love technology and we love software development. You'll find us building API's in .NET, doing DevOps in Ruby, deploying continuously with AWS and creating amazing user experiences for everybody, whether you use our website on your laptop or our app on your mobile device.

name: London Data Visualization
description: Welcome to London Data Visualization! This Meetup group is for people who are interested in learning more about graph visualization, layout, and analysis. Graphs are a fundamental data structure that is used to manage relational information, and they are useful in many application areas such as network topology, link analysis, schematics and models, and in processes, dependencies and flows. Join our Meetup to learn more about a variety of interesting topics including advanced web, desktop, and mobile presentation services for graph interaction and exploration. Learn more about topics of interactive diagramming, advanced geometric work on graph layout, labeling, and routing, and interesting graph analysis methods. In some sessions, we will demonstrate graph visualization systems that are built over many years, and designed to meet discerning industry requirements. We will also regularly feature industry experts, including developers showcasing their production applications, leading professors and students sharing their research, and guest speakers giving talks in specific related fields. The amount of data around us is growing quickly, and more and more, individuals and organizations are relying on graph visualization and analysis to help them discover patterns and hidden relationships within their data. Stay up to date with the latest trends in the visualization field. Join us to learn more, meet new friends, and enjoy a few cocktails!

name: XPRIZE Think Tank London
description:
XPRIZE Think Tanks are local communities that bring together a wide range of people, skills, and experience to work together to make the world a better place. Together we share information and ideas around challenges in the world, new technology, and how technology and community can solve these challenges. We then together as a group to explore how we can make a difference in these areas with the skills, experience, and perspective of our group members.

An XPRIZE Think Tank is more than a set of presentations: we are a community that works to make a practical difference. We hope you come and join us!

name: Progress User Group UK & Ireland (puguk)
description: This is a group for anyone interested in any of the Progress software products, including Openedge and Telerik. It is managed by the UK and Ireland Progress User Group.

name: Dennis Digital DropIn
description: Dennis Digital DropIn (#DennisDigitalDropIn) is an opportunity for individuals to come together and share their experiences about using Drupal, and various other technologies. The meetup is in the format of talks by guest speakers from our teams here on topics such as Drupal, Product Management, PHP, Front End, UI/UX, iOS, Java, Dev Ops, Infrastructure, Training & Audience Development. The DropIn's have a focus on sharing experiences, ideas and solutions to common issues, and improving process around the use of Drupal as a Content Management System and Open Source Technologies in general.

name: Citizen Inventor
description:
www.citizeninventor.com - the overarching community for everything citizen science
www.spacetownhall.com - the space focused initiative of the community 

We are a open and inclusive (online and offline) platform for pushing the boundary of science and engineering via events and projects, by citizen for citizen. We believe in life long ad-hoc learning of science and engineering through doing hands-on projects, with a focus on space technology and exploration in particular.

But before it's too late, let us tell you that Space is a big place and we need all kinds of makers, techies and creatives. We believe everyone knows something - what part can you do in making space colony? Take a small exploration step at a time with us.

If you have any suggestions or feedback, don't hesitate to get in touch: contactme [at] citizeninventor [dot] com

name: MarkLogic User Group London
description: The MarkLogic User Group London is for users and/or fans of MarkLogic and those who are interested in learning more about MarkLogic, XML, XQuery and related technologies. MUGL meetups are free and open to anyone that wishes to attend. There is no formal membership for the group, but you can join our mailing list at http://mugl.org. Meetings are held monthly.

name: Open Data London #ODLmeetup
description:
Calling all open data enthusiasts! Supported by the Open Data Institute, we've set up this group to get together and discuss all things open data related; whether thats open and linked data, open government and transparency, licensing, hosting, research and problem solving, technology, business models, innovation, visualisation and analysis.

If you're a policy maker, researcher, start up or SME using open data, then we'd love to meet you. Further details will follow but if you're interested in giving a talk, or have suggestions or questions then please do get in touch. 

#ODLmeetup

name: PCs & Software Learning for Non-Techies
description:
Calling all non-techie people! Have you ever wanted to learn more about computers and software but thought it too complicated?  Well, this group is just for you. It's aimed squarely at novices and we will learn together in a relaxed, friendly environment at a very easy pace.

Each learning session will be restricted to an organiser and just 3 people (with no geeks allowed) to encourage everyone to interact without embarrassment. Everyone, except the session organiser, will be a beginner so all questions, no matter how silly you think they may be, will be welcomed.

It won’t all be about learning though.  We aim to make every session fun and sociable.  You’ll meet like-minded people and will have an opportunity to connect with other members. 

Initially, we'll start with some simple spreadsheet learning but if this proves popular then more subjects will be added later.  We welcome any suggestions you have for future sessions.

name: Redis London
description: A meetup to discuss Redis in London

name: ~Zero Defects
description: If your software was a jumbo jet, would you fly in it? software is a alive. A living mirror of the team, the customer, the economy, and the technology. The group is about how the community embrace good, bad and ugly ways of working with development, testing, delivery support, and the whole requirements life cycle. We will touch on small and huge projects and share working examples of how not to do things and personal favourites from within the group.

name: Infracoders London
description: This is group for anyone in the London area interested in infrastructure automation. We get together to give demos, share ideas and hack on automation frameworks (e.g. puppet, chef and salt) as well as other related software.

name: Liferay UK User Group
description: I decided to start this group because I realised there must be plenty of people working with Liferay, but there's no real way of getting everyone together to talk just Liferay. The group aims to share and discuss all aspects of Liferay, not just development/techie things and supplement the often sparse documentation by getting people together to help each other learn how the system works, as well as to share ideas to feed back for the future of Liferay. Anyone who works with Liferay in any way should consider joining. I envisage technical meetups at times, but also more general discussions about aspects of social media, etc. --- This is not an official channel but a group of Liferay enthusiasts! ---

name: HPC & GPU Supercomputing Group of London
description: A group for the application of cutting-edge HPC & GPU supercomputing technology to cutting-edge business and academic problems. With an emphasis on the useful application of supercomputing by practitioners, for practitioners. Note: We have sister groups that meet in New York, Boston, Chicago, Silicon Valley, Paris, Seattle, Washington DC, Tokyo, Australia, India, and elsewhere.

name: What is Marketing Automation?
description: Our Mission: To power small Marketing Teams with Big Ambitions! This is a group for anyone interested in Digital Marketing, we will be discussing the benefits Marketing Automation can bring to businesses across Europe. This group is managed by Act-On Software one of the fastest growing digital marketing platforms on the planet! Our solution empowers organisations to engage with buyers across the entire lead-to-revenue process and we’ve done it in a way that offers simplicity and ease-of-use for the marketer. We’ve built a platform that gives small and medium-sized organizations all the value of marketing automation – without the unnecessary complexity of big enterprise systems.

name: UAL Futures meetup
description: Welcome to the UAL Futures meetup group. A space for University of the Arts London students, graduates, staff and alumni inspired by digital media and new technology to meet, connect and collaborate. Creative professionals working in the digital industry and willing to share their expertise and collaborate with our members are also welcome.

name: London Jaspersoft BI Community User Group
description: This is a group for all users and developers interested in Jaspersoft or in Business Intelligence reporting in general. All levels and skills welcome and we are all about sharing knowledge and experience. We are an independent group from TIBCO but we still get them to provide our great venue at Heron Tower (110 Bishopsgate) opposite Liverpool Street tube station. So whether you are an experienced user of Jaspersoft or wanting to find out more - this is the group for you. The group is sponsored and managed by KETL Limited a data integration consultancy.

name: Technology Transformation Network
description:
'Defining DevOps: Development, Operations or More?' was our first Meetup.com event, please check out the video of the evening below:

https://youtu.be/hm4tQOp4oz0


http://www.thettn.tv/headlines/ttn-event-devops-development,-ops-or-more.aspx


The Technology Transformation Network is a thought leadership group formed to bring IT/technology professionals with an interest and passion for disseminating and sharing ideas for IT change and transformation. The TTN physically meets 4 times a year and meetings comprise guest speaker, Q and A, breakout sessions and networking. Membership is moderated to ensure that solely IT professionals are incorporated within the group and also to ensure that sales related discussions are not made and that members are not approached by sales people. The TTN is a sister network to the global leading group the HR Transformation Network. We hope that you enjoy the group and please ask if you have any questions related to it.

name: London Data Science Journal Club
description:
Keeping up with the latest research is important for the data scientist so let's work on this together. Each week or two, we will choose one or more articles to read and meet up to discuss them. This group is open to data scientists of any experience level and speciality but I expect the core group will be relatively small. I hope you are as excited about data science, machine learning, and statistics research as I am, and I look forward to meeting you!

This is a variety of the Silicon Valley Data Science Journal Club and we will be closely following the pages that they read.

http://www.meetup.com/Silicon-Valley-Data-Science-Journal-Club/

name: Hazelcast User Group London (HUGL)
description:
Find out more about the leading open source in memory data grid (IMDG)!

Enjoy some refreshments.

Meet other amazing Java technologists working on ultrascale high frequency application development across Finance, Energy, Telco, Gaming, Travel, eCommerce, Mobile, Media, Web, Saas/Cloud and all other walks of life.

The Hazelcast User Group London (HUGL) is the place to be. Hazelcast is being used to solve many system scalability and massive compute problems across all sectors. Join us if you'd like to learn more about Hazelcast and meet people using Hazelcast as their IMDG. www.hazelcast.org

name: Bayesian networks London
description: This is a group for anyone interested in Bayesian networks (Belief Networks) and more general probabilistic graphical models. Speakers will be invited to give interesting, detailed talks that can be understood by all. We hope to cover topical subjects such as 'Deep belief networks', 'Bayesian networks and Big data', 'Multi-agent Bayesian networks for the Internet of things', and welcome all ideas.

name: West London Developers and Entrepreneurs
description: This group brings together developers, designers and entrepreneurs to make their dreams come alive. We are all driven by our ideas and are motivated to bring them to life. The journey is much more fun with others, so come along and see who's there. Developers can find future partners to commercially grow their ideas, while entrepreneurs can collaborate with tech or design prodigy's to build their ideas into products that customers will love.

name: Artificial Intelligence Meetup - London
description: Clearly coming years are the most exciting times in Artificial Intelligence. This group is focused on New tech stacks available in AI and the use cases around 'AI'. We will invite exciting startups who are working in 'AI' and present their technology.

name: London DataTech Startups
description:
Calling all interested in DataTech.
This group is for Data and Analytics startups, data scientists, investors, corporates, analytics leaders and any other interested parties to network and collaborate on building great businesses. We will have presentations, demos, workshops and more.
This group is run by Venturr.com.
Sign up and be the first to know of upcoming events.

name: {"Waltham Forest" : "Tech"}
description: With the reality that not everyone in the Tech community lives in Old street, I thought it was time to bring the development talk closer to home. The idea of this group is for likeminded developers to meet and chat about what they love over some quality craft beer (soft drinks if you like). All development practices and languages welcome. Bring your problems, solutions or just come to listen.

name: AWS  High Performance Computing (HPC) London Meet Up
description: This group is for IT & Business professionals with an interest in learning more about running High Performance Computing workloads on the AWS cloud, this will be a cross industry vertical community. Aiming for 1st meet up in Q1 2016. For more background information : https://aws.amazon.com/hpc/ https://aws.amazon.com/hpc/cfncluster/

name: London Groovy & Grails User Group
description:
The London GGUG is a user group dedicated to the Groovy language and its ecosystem of tools and frameworks, in particular the web framework Grails. We meet on the first Tuesday of every month at SkillsMatter so pop along and meet fellow Groovy & Grails enthusiasts.

Follow the group on twitter at @LondonGGUG.

name: London Mesos User Group
description:
Apache Mesos simplifies the development and operation of resource efficient distributed applications. According to Chris Fry, SVP of Engineering at Twitter Mesos is one of the primary keys to their data centre efficiency. 


Mesos can already run a wide range of existing distributed technologies including, Hadoop, Spark and Storm. In addition there is a growing ecosystem of frameworks built just for Mesos such as Chronos created by aribnb as distributed cron replacement and Marathon for running longer running applications.

name: 'DR DRinks' Meetup London
description: This group is for anyone interested in new trends in IT, that want to meet like-minded people in a non formal environment, over a couple of beers (or soft drinks) on a monthly basis in London. Hosted by Zerto, a software company specialising in Disaster Recovery and Business Continuity solutions.

name: Evolution of IoT toward  IoT Ecosystems - London Meetup
description:
An ecosystem is a complex web of interdependent agents and relationships aimed to create and allocate personal and business value. The need for integration between intelligent devices , people and enterprises capabilities has become even more critical. Innovation, availability of big data, accesses to personal contexts and contexts evolution are some of the key drivers solution of humans and objects ecological communities. The current challenges in certain sectors, such as Health, Fitness, Energy and Environment, have created the need not only for integration, but a true network of distribute controls and information exchange. The new age of ecosystems In today’s digital world requires new technologies, a broad use of Big Data and Analytics Consumers are forming an ever-more insatiable desire for sophisticated and compelling experiences in all aspects of their lives.
To make real every mentioned we need an evolution of cloud architectural solution based on a system bus that manages messages in real time. To a higher level, agents are aggregated and integrated in groups that constitute the ecosystems.

Meetup scope
We want to create an active group to analyze the specific aspects of Ecosystems, IoT and Personal Big Data science. The objective is to discuss how a person can have a generalizable extraction of knowledge and recommendation from personal cloud data generated by his devices to improve the everyday life quality where the personal cloud is integrated in an ecosystem. The purpose of meetup is explore such complexities creating capabilities in a new and fascinating IT field.

name: London OpenShift User Group
description:
We ae the London OpenShift user group. We meet regularly for talks and discussions on all topics related to OpenShift. Join if you are interested in learning what OpenShift is, how people are using it and to meet other people with experience using Openshift.


OpenShift is Red Hat's Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS) that allows developers to quickly develop, host, and scale applications in a cloud environment. With OpenShift you have choice of offerings, including online, on premise, and open source project options.

name: CentOS Users and Contributers in UK
description: This is a group for anyone using, contributing or looking at starting with CentOS Linux. This includes emerging technologies like containers, cloud, high performance, super computing and associated applications. We are going to focus on face to face meetups regularly, and organise demos, tutorials and talks around things interesting to this audience.

name: London BotRace - Game AI Hackathon
description: This group will meet regularly to run game AI bot challenges. Each competition begins with a set of game rules and the technical details for hooking up your bot. You then go off - alone or in groups - and write a bot to compete against the other teams. Each round is scored and the first round starts right away. The competition lasts for less than a day. So hurry up and start coding!

name: Telco Technology Professionals
description:
This is an invite only group for Technology Professionals working in Telecoms in the London and the M4 corridor areas.

 

This group aims to provide networking with others doing embedded software, Element/Network Management Software, OSS/BSS, Service Management Software, Big Data and any other systems that support the Telecoms industry.

 

This group is being kept private to ensure the quality of the meetup - no recruitment agents or sales people.

name: London IT Managed Service Provider
description:
The MSP Place is the only way for the UK's IT service providers to meet up and discuss new opportunities, in an enjoyable, yet focussed environment. 

• No vendors

• No distis.

• No end-users.

• Only MSPs! 

The MSP Place is built on the idea that when successful service providers work within an established ecosystem, the only logical outcome can be more business opportunities for all. 

At the MSP Place, we are all experts in something. However, let's face it - there are always occasions where we can't fulfil our customer needs alone... Lost opportunities... Therefore, the purpose of this group is to win new opportunities. 

By coming together and broadening our individual expertise, the obvious result will be more deals closed and happier customers; without the risk or hassle of engaging unknown suppliers. 

The MSP Place will host a monthly meet up in the City of London. 

The venue will always be informal with a few drinks so that we can put faces to names and names to business opportunities. 

We will become a community based on trust, where strong relationships will be forged for the purposes of long term commercial collaboration. 

The MSP Place: A direct route to new business.

name: HR/Talent Analytics Meetup
description:
The purpose of the HR Analytics meetup is to gather together people interested in using data to improve how HR decisions are made, or improve the way in which people are managed.  


If you are an HR professional who would like to understand how you can start using data to improve your professional life, or an analyst/data scientist who is interested in hearing more about this growing industry, or someone building technology in the space - or just someone curious, please do sign up and join us.


From beginners in this space, to the revolutionaries trying to disrupt the HR/talent sector, we want you all involved!


p.s. HR analytics, talent analytics, workforce analytics, people analytics... We're going to go ahead and consider them all the same thing :)


See you soon!

name: Drupal Kent
description:
Come and meet up with other people in Kent who are into Drupal or are just interested. An informal event to which all are welcome: developers, designers, hobbyists, business users, people considering Drupal.

If you are interested, get in touch!

name: JBoss User Group
description:
JBUG London is a group of people who share a common interest in JBoss software.

JBUG is organised and supported by the community, we meet on a regular basis to discuss new technologies, development methodologies, interesting use cases, and other technical topics in friendly and casual atmosphere (usually with some beer and pizza).Our goal is to provide education and help, to promote open source, to network and share real world experiences with other members of the community.

If you would like to meet face-to-face with other members, please join the group and respond to one of our upcoming events. As this is a user group we are looking for people out there to volunteer to talk about their experiences with any JBoss.org project. If you have something that you would like to talk about then feel free to contact the organisers and ask to give a short lightning talk at the next meeting. Tell us about something you think is cool, something you think is rubbish, problems you've encountered and would like solving or problems you’ve solved and you’d like to share - anything JBoss related is what we want.

Similarly, if you've got any questions or need some more information about JBUG London, don't hesitate to contact one of the organisers.

 

London JBUG is sponsored and organised by C2B2 Consulting Limited - The Leading Independent Middleware Experts.

name: London Ribbonfarm Readers
description:
Meet and chat with fellow Ribbonfarm readers in London.

Like a book club where half the group haven't read the book, you don't need to have actually read Ribbonfarm in a while. If you have something interesting to contribute to the conversation, you're welcome.

name: The Official OpenCart London Meetup
description:
OpenCart, Realex Payments and Welford Media will be hosting a series of Meetup's dedicated to OpenCart developers and merchants in London, UK. Completely free of charge, these OpenCart Meetup's and training sessions will give OpenCart enthusiasts the unique chance to learn about the latest additions to the OpenCart system from developers who helped to design and build them. 


We ran the first OpenCart Meetup on the 12th of February which covered: 

• In-depth technical overview of OpenCart 2.0 

• Extended Q&A session with the OpenCart Team 

• One-on-one training opportunities 

• Networking opportunities with other developers 

• Free food and beer! 


The next session will be on the 11th of June and the agenda is as follows: 

• Great networking opportunities 

• Free food and beer! 

• How you can keep on top of your store’s SEO 

• What you can do to increase your online presence 

• Relaxed workshop giving you the chance to get hands-on advice 

• One-on-one training opportunities 

Sign-up quick because places are limited and do run out!

name: London Startup: Idea to IPO
description:
Entrepreneurship permeates the culture of Silicon Valley - the innovation capital of the world. 

The advent of the Digital Age has democratized innovation and entrepreneurship. 

Never before has it been more possible for anyone from anywhere, with a great idea and a burning desire to succeed, to make it big, and in the process, change the world in a relatively short period of time. 

HP, Intel, Apple, Microsoft, Cisco, Oracle, Yahoo, eBay, Amazon, Google, Facebook and many, many, many other iconic companies all started with just an idea. Taking a startup from idea to IPO has taken on mythical proportions in Silicon Valley and beyond. Many dream the dream, with hopes of launching the "next big thing". 

We are a community of entrepreneurs, technologists, engineers, venture capitalists, angel investors, educators, financial professionals, corporate executives, attorneys, academics, bloggers, writers, content creators, and social activists. 

Our mission is to provide entrepreneurs with the knowledge, guidance, tools, and connections they need to succeed. Our goal is to build a strong, vibrant, collaborative entrepreneurial community with deep, lasting business and social relationships from Silicon Valley to London and beyond.

name: Data & Analytics Innovation & Entrepreneurship
description: This is a group for professionals , entrepreneurs , investors, academics & researchers interested in the rapidly growing field of Business Analytics, Information , Big Data , decision sciences and related technologies that enable decisions. The business of enabling decisions is going thru transformation with continued digitalisation of businesses and evolution of technology in Big Data, Analytics, Mobile, Social, Cloud, Sensors. Evolution of Digital enterprise, initiatives of Smart Cities, Open Data and Digital Healthcare etc. are leading to several new models of consumption and value delivery from data and information. At the same time the original challenges of enabling competitive edge and deriving business value from Business Analytics and Information remain . There is also a disparity in the level of adoption by mid Tier organisations, social sector Government where it can make huge difference. There are challenges from a legal and security perspective as well that need tackling. In a rapidly growing space like this there are several whitespaces for innovation and entrepreneurship. Lets get together and leverage our collective experience and initiatives to shape and build systems, innovation ideas, share experiences, network and create new value propositions or simply learn from or guide, mentor .....over a drink!

name: Docker London
description:
Meet other developers and ops engineers using Docker. Docker is an open platform for developers and sysadmins to build, ship, and run distributed applications. Consisting of Docker Engine, a portable, lightweight runtime and packaging tool, and Docker Hub, a cloud service for sharing applications and automating workflows, Docker enables apps to be quickly assembled from components and eliminates the friction between development, QA, and production environments. As a result, IT can ship faster and run the same app, unchanged, on laptops, data center VMs, and any cloud.

Learn more about Docker at http://www.docker.com

name: NSOfficeHours
description: NSOfficeHours is a meetup that welcomes people of all skill levels to grab a laptop, hang out, and code. It's for people to help each other learn, improve their skills, and to help fix bugs in projects. If we can't answer your question, we'll find you someone who can, or at least point you in the right direction.

name: Google Cloud Platform
description: We here to work people that build stuff. Our main focus will be around Google Cloud Platform products like Compute Engine, App Engine, Cloud SQL, Cloud Storage, Cloud Datastore and BigQuery. We welcome everybody from product managers trying to help their developer team move fast to an php developer see how can get a startup idea off the ground with App Engine. We will work with the local Google Developer Group to be part of the bigger Google Community.

name: Data Science London
description:
Data Science London - We're the largest #datascience community in Europe

We are a community of data scientists, data geeks and data hackers that meets regularly to discuss data science methods, topics, tools & technologies. 

We promote free, open, dissemination of data science knowledge.  

We are totally independent and not affiliated to any brand or vendor.

We discuss topics like: data science, data mining, machine learning, machine intelligence, deep learning, predictive analytics, artificial intelligence, big data analytics, NLP and statistical analysis and more....

We encourage data science peer-to-peer learning & sharing, collaboration among data scientists and data startups. We also promote open source data science tools.

Follow us on twitter@ds_ldn

Read our blog www.datasciencelondon.com

This is a meetup for hands-on people directly involved in data science projects.

Please note: Absolutely no recruiters, HR people, Sales & Marketing people, Events & Conference people, brokers or agents. No exceptions.

name: London 3D printers
description:
We look at design and making things with a focus on the use of 3D Printing, CNC and additive manufacturing technology.

Our workshops will cover the basics of 3D printing, the machines, technology and aspects of the design process (with plenty of opportunity for networking too!)

Come and join the digital manufacturing revolution!

name: London.dev
description:
Welcome to London.dev Meetup. 

London.dev is aimed at professionals within the web industry who have an interest in Software development, and/or Computer science.  It happens usually the last Tuesday of every Month.

We are looking for volunteers, speakers, partners, sponsors and nice places to host the event. We like to work with other meetups and conferences too. If you are interested in or have some idea about, please contact us.

Thanks to our partners London IT Contractors Group and ProgSCon Conference to help us to organise this meetup.


Thanks for reading, and see you at our next meetup.

Follow us on twitter: @londondev_mtp

name: Big Data Debate
description:
The Big Data Debate is run by import.io with the ambition to gather like-minded professionals together and discuss relevant and timely topics in big data.

Meetups are held once a month so come along and enjoy a beer or two!

The group is unbiased and does not advocate the use of any specific brand or technology. We remain impartial and act as an information and networking hub for all contenders in the industry.

*NOTE: This Meetup is intended for prospective Meetup applicants only -- no recruiters, please.

name: Proactive Developers
description: This meetup group is for passionate technology enthusiasts that enjoy sharing and learning from others about a wide range of topics in software development. It's for anyone wanting to learn about cool technologies, great working practices and developing their career through engaging events and practical sessions. The ultimate aim of this group is to bring together passionate technologists who want to have fun meeting like minded people and maybe pick up a skill or two in the process!

name: Predictive Analytics London Meetup
description: This group is for all those interested in using predictive analytics to identify patterns in the large amount of data now available. It's a place to share challenges, experiences and best practices. Any skills levels are welcome!

name: Financial Planning, Performance Management & BI Meetup
description:
This group is for those involved professionally in financial planning, business planning, financial performance management, business intelligence, business analysis, data visualisation, predictive analytics, and driving business efficiency and improvement. Relevant job titles include MD, FD, CFO, Financial Controller, Finance Officer, Accountant, Business Analyst, Business Planning Officer, BI Consultant, and similar.

We will be arranging networking meetups for as specific events about relevant topics to your business.

To show we mean business, our first event is a breakfast briefing at the Royal Exchange on Financial Performance Management in collaboration with IBM and Assimil8 - breakfast is on us!! There is no cost to attend.

name: LondonR
description:
LondonR meetings provide an opportunity for people to learn and to share information about R. The sessions consists of 3-4 short presentations followed by a networking session and drinks. We are always looking for presenters and new members are always welcome. This is a free event!

For more information on this event please visit - www.londonr.org

LondonR is organised and sponsored by Mango Solutions. Mango is a data analysis software company offering application development, consultancy, training and support.  We are R experts and enthusiasts, with a  wealth of experience of R in the commercial sector.  Information about us can be found at  www.mango-solutions.com

name: London RecSys
description:
The aim of this group is to build a network of people interested in recommender systems and give them a forum for presenting and discussing ideas.

We are a mixed group of people from research, industry, education, design and startups. If you have an interest in recommender systems, come and join us.

name: Gaming Analytics London
description: Based on the success of the first Gaming Analytics Summit in London in March 2016, we want to provide a platform where data executives/analysts/gamer enthusiasts can unite throughout the year to share unique insight and hear from leading pioneers within the industry.

name: Big Data Jobs
description:
Hi Big Data enthusiasts my names Nathan,

I'm a regular attendee at many of the Big Data meet ups decided this rapidly expanding space is in need of some hiring solutions to help both employers and employees find suitable matches in confidence. So please, if you’re on here or your employee is it doesn’t mean you/they are looking but you may be contacted by someone who is!

I hope people will just use it just like any other job board but it’s free and with the benefit of it being our market specific and having a meet up within. The meet ups will be like a job fair and an opportunity to network and learn from each other.

The purpose of this group will be to aid and benefit those seeking a new opportunity in Big Data or as an employer, where you can find your next hire or advertise your job in our discussions column. I would be interested in speaking to Universities and trainers who could help us educate the next Data Scientists too. 

Be your search active or passive, I hope this group will help you satisfy all your needs. For any help or advice please feel free to contact me: Nathan.laidlaw@gcsltd.comor call 01189 563 900.

Follow us on Twitter: @bigdatajobs1

name: SaltStack user group - London
description:
A meetup for systems administrators, site reliability engineers, data center operators, DevOps-minded folks, SaltStack customers, users and contributors. SaltStack is software used for enterprise-scale infrastructure automation, cloud orchestration and application deployment and configuration management. The Salt open source software project was written in Python and according to GitHub is one of the largest and most active open source projects in the world. SaltStack is used by Web-scale IT organizations like LinkedIn, Hulu, Salesforce.com, NASA JPL, Clemson University, Photobucket, XMission, and thousands more. 

We are looking for group members who are interested in sharing and participating by giving talks and SaltStack use case demonstrations and by sharing lessons learned and good SaltStack practices. Please let us know if you'd be willing to give a talk at an upcoming SaltStack London meetup, or request a topic that you'd like to be addressed.

name: H2O Big Data Science London
description: This meetup is about sharing knowledge & learning the latest developments about statistics, machine learning, math, analytics, parallel algorithms, distributed systems.
