We will do hands on work with Data and invite experts in the space to discuss practical and theoretical aspects of doing data science with big data using H2O.

name: The London PaaS User Group (LOPUG)
description:
Platform as a Service (PaaS) is the future of developer-centric cloud deployment. Our user group brings together people who are involved in building and using PaaS clouds to share their experiences, war stories and to work together shape an open future for PaaS.

Follow us at LOPUG

name: Python for Quant Finance
description: This group is about the use of Python for Quantitative Financial Applications and Interactive Financial Analytics.

name: OpenSource & Agile Community Events
description:
What Topics?

- Scala, F#, Haskell, Clojure, Python, Java, Ruby & C#

- Agile, Kanban, Software Craftsmanship, BDD, TDD, CI/CD

- Architecture, Microservices, CQRS, DDD

- NOSQL, Neo4J, MongoDB, Cassandra, Riak, CouchDB

- Mobile, Android, iOS, Internet of Things

- HTML5, JavaScript, NodeJS...

What kind of events?

We organise talks, meet ups, hackathons, conferences, courses and any other type of gathering that helps our community learn and share skills to write better software.

We curate content for our 'own' In-the-Brain Series, which feature the world's leading innovators and experts, who like to share their brain and inventions with you through their talks. In addition, we host approximately 40 meet up groups on a wide range of topics, who curate their own content and speakers, and which we support by providing our venue and by recording their talks as SkillsCasts, which are recordings of film, code and slides of every talk. We publish these SkillsCasts the next day, and they are free to watch for our members on our community website http://skillsmatter.com (and membership is free).

We also organise short conferences, which we call eXchanges, usually very specialised, aimed to give a certain idea, innovation or technology a 'push' by enabling a dedicated, passionate community to meet up, exchange ideas for projects, cooperation and learn.

Finally, we organise training courses, aimed at passionate enterprise developers, architects and project managers who want to learn new technologies and agile practices, straight from the source - our courses are authored and taught by well-known experts, often the creators of the course's subject.

You can find out more about Skills Matter on http://skillsmatter.com

Hope to see you at one of our events soon!

name: This Happened London
description:
Founded in 2007 by Chris O’Shea, Joel Gethin Lewis and Andreas Müller. Now run by Kate Pincott.

This Happened is a series of events focusing on the stories behind interaction design. Having ideas is easier than making them happen. We delve into projects that exist today, how their concepts and production process can help inform future work.

Our talks happen all over the world and this is the London one! 

JOIN US:  https://www.facebook.com/ThisHappenedLondon

FOCUS IS:  Interaction Design & Technology

If you are any kind of maker, tinker, hacker or like seeing how things are made, you will enjoy hearing designers tell the story of the making process and learning from their experience. 

OUR PREVIOUS TALKS: http://vimeo.com/thlondon/videos

name: London - Cambridge Coding Academy
description: Launch creative ideas into reality through coding. Meet friends, learn industry relevant programming techniques and develop unique skills in high demand through hands-on workshops taught by Cambridge graduates. Simply pick the workshop that fits your purpose and start coding - http://cambridgecoding.com/signup-london

name: UK - High Performance Computing
description:
An established MeetUp group for people in the UK interested in various aspects of high performance computing (HPC). Including GPU, cloud, cluster and virtualization. From industries as broad as Broadcast, Gaming to scientific and financial.

Novices to Experts welcome. Post new ideas for a meetup.

name: Spark London
description: A group for users of Apache Spark. We are a diverse bunch of Data Engineers, Data Scientist and Machine Learning practitioners. Experienced users as well as novices are welcome.

name: London Erlang User Group
description: The Erlang User Group is a group of Erlang enthusiasts who are interested in sharing their knowledge and meeting people who share similar interests. The group is open to Erlang Architects, Programmers, Project Managers, Software and Platform Innovators, and existing Erlang users as well as Erlang newbies and anyone interested in Erlang. We arrange and promote regular events involving Erlang including free seminars and workshops, followed by the customary Erlounge.

name: Software Circus London
description:
We are a motley crew of dreamers who are unhealthily obsessed with consuming information and changing ourselves and those around us. We love software, tech and anything (from any discipline) that is going to change the world. Apart from our wider focus, we believe that meetups should be a lot of fun where laughing out loud and meeting new people is built in, not an opt-in extra.

At Software Circus meetups you can expect two things:

• A broad range of subjects, perfectly suited to the discerning expert-generalist

• More 'meet'ing and less listening

And since it's a circus it has to be fun too of course.

name: Deep Learning London Meetup
description:
The aim of this group is to bring together people interested in the family of machine learning methods that are concerned with learning distributed, hierarchical ("deep") representations. Neural Networks being the most popular implementation. 

The format will be based around guest speakers sharing new research ideas and applications covering a wide range of fields from computer vision and natural language processing to autonomous systems and prognostics.

Persontyle has started this community as part of their wider initiative for people to learn the art and science of turning data into meaningful insights. The vision is for this group to be an open platform for people to share knowledge, practices, research, applications and critiques of deep learning.

We are always on the lookout for interesting speakers and topics. If interested, get in touch.

Twitter:  @deeplearningldn

Hashtag: #deeplearningldn

name: Data Visualization London
description: Gathering of people who are interested in data visualization. Speaker series - watch and listen to fellow designers, statisticians, mathematicians, architects, programmers, start ups, and other great people in the industry. Have a cool data visualization to show? Questions to ask? Want to meet others who have a data driven mindset? Let's meetup and talk d3/Gephi Bringing together data visualizers across London.

name: Big Data Developers in London
description: This is an IBM sponsored Big Data meetup group. Geared towards developers, data scientists and ALL Big Data enthusiasts. Our Meetups typically include two or three 30-45 min presentations that serve as an introduction and overview for a specific Big Data technology. It is followed by ~2 hours to collaborate and network with fellow developers. Our meetups are FREE. Meetup topics include: - Hadoop-based analytics - Stream (Real-time) Computing - Spark - Text Analytics - Visualisation and Discovery tools for Big Data - Big Data App Development - Predictive Analytics - Machine Learning - Cognitive analysis techniques - Deep dives into the technologies that makes big data processing possible - Anything and everything about Big Data. Join us today.

name: Enterprise Search London Meetup
description:
Enterprise Search London is a meetup for anyone interested in building search and discovery experiences — from intranet search and site search, to advanced discovery applications and beyond.

Disclaimer: This meetup is NOT about SEO or search engine marketing.

What people are saying:

  • "Join this meetup if you have a passion for enterprise search and user experience that you would like to share with other able-minded practitioners." — Vegard Sandvold
  • "Full marks for vision and execution. Looking forward to the next Meetup." — Martin White
  • “Consistently excellent” — Helen Lippell

Past speakers:

  • Stephen Arnold, Arnold IT
  • Martin Belam, The Guardian
  • Jeremy Bentley, SmartLogic
  • Stephen Dunn, The Guardian
  • Gregory Grefenstette, Exalead
  • Jon Handler, Amazon CloudSearch
  • Charlie Hull, Flax
  • Grant Ingersoll, LucidWorks
  • Udo Kruschwitz, Essex University
  • Stefan Olafsson, Twigkit
  • Lee Pollington, MarkLogic
  • Tony Russell-Rose, Endeca
  • Vegard Sandvold, Comperio
  • Martina Schell, Travelmatch.co.uk
  • Graham Tackley, The Guardian
  • Tyler Tate, Twigkit
  • Upayavira, SourceSense
  • Martin White, Intranet Focus
  • Max Wilson, Swansea University

name: Hackathons and Jams UK
description:
For those of us that enjoy participating in hackathons and jams - where we create and compete to produce the next big thing that will change the world... even if it's just a little bit at a time.

Important

RSVPing 'Yes' to our meetup.com group does not grant you entry to an event. You MUST follow the links in the event description to sign up on each hackathon's dedicated signup page.

name: London Open Source Search Social
description: There's a massive pool of search technology expertise and experience in London (and nearby), but it's currently locked away in mailing lists and cubicles. We want to bring some of that out into the open to share war stories, advice, and business cards over a quiet beer.

name: SumoLogic User Group
description:
All Sumo Logic users
All SumoLogic interested parties
All those who have an interest in Big Data Analytics and Cloud based solutions

name: Fab Lab London Meetup
description: We’re a 4000 sq.ft. creative space that provides open and membership based access to digital fabrication tools, education workshops, making events and a vibrant community. We help individuals and companies learn about the application of digital technologies, rapid hardware prototyping, 3D printing and sustainable design practices. The Meetup group is for the events we're hosting at the Fab Lab.

name: DigitalOcean London
description:
Meet software developers of all skill levels to share resources, learn, and form discussions around technical topics. 

This meetup is for London developers, by London developers — send Sammy a message if you'd like to help organise or give a talk!

Join the DigitalOcean Community to learn more, and please read our Events Code of Conduct.

DigitalOcean is the world’s fastest growing cloud computing platform built for developers. Our mission is simple: we’re passionate about making complex infrastructure simple and delighting our customers with a seamless experience that brings them joy. New users can easily deploy a blazing fast cloud server with an intuitive control panel interface, or on a larger scale with the company's straightforward API.

name: London Magento Users Group
description: Come and share your experiences with Magento or Magento2 with other users and developers. Meet local developers, potential clients, network, trade stories, hints and tips.

name: London QlikView Developers Group
description: We will share great ideas, use cases and innovations from using QlikView software for work or personal use to generate ideas for future development. Examples from anywhere and everywhere are welcome from simple data visualisations to predictive modelling, extensions or server performance tuning.

name: London React User Group
description:
This group was established by Red Badger, a software company at Old Street.

React is already having a huge impact on the way we think about Web UI development at Red Badger and this is an opportunity to learn why and share your own experiences.

We meet once a month, usually on the 3rd Wednesday of each month 

We generally have 2 or 3 speakers and loads of questions, pizzas and beer.

We are a sociable group and very welcoming to newcomers. Follow us on Twitter @Londonreact and join the conversation on Slack here

See you soon!

name: London Applied ML & AI Meetup
description: This Meetup is about actually DOING AI and ML. AI and ML is moving from academia to mainstream and this user group is going to be riding that wave. In this regular, London-based evening Meetup you’ll see talks by everyone from developers, theorists and technology specialists that dive through how to apply machine learning, particularly deep learning, algorithms to real-world use cases. In particular, we will be examining various deep learning toolkits and applying them to analyze actual data sets. Laptops will be required for the practical workshops, but this will be announced before the Meetup. The emphasis here is on actually applying AI and ML, from the coal face.

name: HTML5 CodeShow London
description:
Welcome to the html5 Codeshow! We are a group of hackers/developers/tech enthusiasts who are ecstatic about what the future of the web and mobile apps will bring. For years we've seen what the future might look like via sexy sci-fi films--well now the future is here and it's our turn to make that vision a reality! Join us in sharing our coding knowledge and let's develop ideas together over pizza and beer!

Are you working on a website, mobile web app, or designing a game? What are some of the challenges you’ve encountered that you will need to overcome in order to finish the project? Did you just have a breakthrough moment and would like to share it with the rest of the group? Maybe you’re looking for collaborators or just feedback from fellow hackers?

With a strong emphasis on best practices and problem-solving, this HTML5 meetup series aims at inviting developers to demo projects and interact with an audience of fellow programmers. The goal is to get your questions answered!  We will bring at least one expert speaker on board per session, but we want to keep this meetup really developer-centric.

Everyone is welcome to present at the next CodeShow as long as it's HTML5 related - we only ask you to keep it within 5-7 minutes and to let us know in advance if you wish to present (via personal message or in the comments)

This fun geek event will be as good as we all make it! Bring your hacks and your friends and join us for a night of html5 and its CSS3/javascript/flash/.etc friends!

Look forward to seeing you all there!

name: Splunk Dev London
description: This is a group for anyone, in the Greater London area, who is interested in learning about and sharing ideas about developing apps in Splunk.

name: NW London Hackers & Makers
description: This group is for people who are interested in creating a hub for hackers, makers and more in North West London. All are welcome.

name: Cassandra London
description:
A group for users of Apache Cassandra to meet and discuss the popular "NoSQL" database.

If you use Apache Cassandra in a production environment, or you are thinking about using it, you should come along to learn from others in the same boat.

http://cassandra.apache.org/

name: London Power BI Users Group
description:
Power BI is the new service from Microsoft that is creating a real buzz in the analytics and business intelligence community.  Business users can get data from almost any source, visualise it and share their insights.  It also has great power under the covers to do sophisticated data preparation and modelling and build beautiful dashboards. Users can ask questions of their data with natural language and Power BI will do it's best to answer you .

This group will help you get started with Power BI.  We'll offer a mix of introductory talks but we'll also have some sessions for the experts as well.  Some of the events will be hands-on. 

We meet monthly in Central London on a weekday evening.  Please come along - you will be sure of a warm welcome from the organisers

Power BI is relatively new but already has 5 million subscribers - we'll show you why!

The London Power BI Users Group is part of the Microsoft Power BI User Group Program. Microsoft is not responsible for content on this website or activities that take place at Group meetings.

name: AngularJS - Watch this space
description: We're not entirely sure yet. Figuring out if there's an appetite for yet another AngularJS Group

name: UK OSS on Windows Azure Platform Meetup
description: This group is open to anyone interested in discussing running Linux and OpenSource Software (OSS) on the Azure platform. "Microsoft ♥ Linux"

name: London Eclipse User Group
description: This is a group for developers and users interested in Eclipse Technology and Eclipse Working Groups for LocationTech, Science, IoT and others.

name: ANDchat
description: Our ANDchat meetup provides digital enthusiasts with the opportunity to join up-close and personal debates around a range of relevant and trending topics. Each "chat" is led by a member of our high-profile tech guru community, all offering a wealth of industry experience as input to the conversation. There will be plenty of time for informal networking at the top and tail of each event, with beers and pizza on the house. Be sure to sign up for your seat as spaces are limited!

name: Talend London & S.East Meetup - Hadoop/Spark/ETL/MDM/etc.
description: Calling out to all Talend and Big data enthusiasts! Talend 6.0 has just launched with all the usual brilliance around ETL, Data Quality, ESB and Master Data Management. But the big data element have taken a massive leap forward with it being the first tool to support spark and spark streaming natively. We would love to have a meetup to share ideas and stories about how to get the best out Talend (open source and enterprise) and how to really get into the new area of Spark. We'll meet once a month in Holborn as its so central - downstairs bar at XXXX - 5.30 - 8pm. Key thing is to meet people, share ideas, learn new things and have a few beers while doing it.

name: UK Azure User Group
description: The UK Azure User Group. Meeting monthly for evenings and weekly for mornings to discuss and consult on Microsoft's Azure cloud computing platform; held in London, Birmingham and other locations in the UK.

name: ThoughtWorks London Tech Talks
description:
This group provides insightful talks and examples to showcase the real-life, complex issues ThoughtWorks helps their clients solve, and the innovative paths they take.

The talks will be mainly technical, but you don't have to be a techie to join! If you want to hear about cool technologies and how they get applied in innovative ways to solve real problems, you're more than welcome to be part of our events! 

RSVP and come say hi! :-)

name: Women Hack For Non Profits
description:
Women Hack For Non-Profits is a community of women in technology, who write open source software for non-profits with a social cause. With this initiative we aim to not only increase open source foot print of women in technology but also help non profits solve technology challenges they face. We do not charge non profits for help we provide but we ask in return they respect our time and commitment.

You do not have to code to join us, you just need to be a woman in tech or interested in tech. Projects need help in all aspects, QA, PM, UI, UX, front end, backend, blogging, social media. Everything and anything. 

With this initiative we also aim to provide women tools and workshops that could help them learn and acquire new skills.

name: Drupal Tech City London
description: Meet fellow Drupalers, open source enthusiasts and web developers in Tech City (East London, Shoreditch) area.

name: The London Django Meetup Group
description:
The London Django Meetup Group is a social meetup, we regularly hold a gathering the 2nd Tuesday of each month.

The meetups are an occasion for all, you don't have to be a veteran Django developer, although an interest in Django and web development is advisable. :)

Meetup notes + videos are collected on GitHub, for August 2014 onwards. If you have slides/notes to add please send in a pull request! https://github.com/djangolondon/The-Django-...

PS: Sometimes Anand likes bringing delicious Django pony cakes... so be advised!

name: PHP Zend Framework Tribe of London
description:
Are you a Zend Framework enthusiast / coder / hacker / rainmaker / entrepreneur? This group is for all those in the London area who want to meet others involved in Zend Framework projects and development.

We're plugged into both Silicon Roundabout and Silicon Hill and will hold regular drinks / discussions / workshops / hackathons... specifically tailored to the needs of Zenders.

So whether you're a Zend expert, someone who wants to get into it, or a non-techie looking to work with Zenders, this is the Meetup for you. Feel free to share your ideas for events and to suggest meet dates.

Note: To protect the coherence of the group, posting by recruiters and agencies and open soliciting at events is not looked upon positively. This is a Meetup for solid discussions of tech issues and business ideas.

name: London Amazon CloudSearch Group
description: This group will focus on the use of Amazon CloudSearch for the development and deployment of search applications. Amazon CloudSearch is a fully-managed search service in the AWS cloud that allows customers to easily integrate fast and highly scalable search functionality into their applications. Meetup presentations and discussions will cover topics such as: User case studies and lessons learned Getting started with CloudSearch Ranking and relevance tuning Working with other AWS services This group is for anyone interested in search technology - such as search developers, web application developers, architects, IT, and search application users.

name: Bot Builders and Conversation Designers London
description:
This is a group for anyone interested in bots and conversational interfaces. Whether you're an engineer, a designer, a content person, PM or founder this is a space where you can get to know others interested in the topic and keep up with the latest developments. Things we'll cover include conversational commerce, conversation design, botkit, hubot, wit.ai and anything else you suggest.

I'll organise the first meetup once there are a few members in the group.

name: Front Endgineers London
description:
The Front Endgineers is a group for Software Engineers with an interest in Front End technologies. Through our forum and regular meetings you can keep in touch with the latest industry developments, learn new technologies, meet other developers, discuss technical/non technical issues and network further throughout the community.

FAQ

What is the Front Endgineers group?
What goes on in the Front Endgineers?
Who can join?
Is there a fee to Join, is there a fee for the events?
How do I join?
Do you have to go to every presentation/event?


What is the Front Endgineers group?

The Front Endgineers is a technical user group for software engineers based in London. It was founded in October 2013.

What goes on in the Front Endgineers?

We are hoping to run a variety of regular events ranging from social events to technical presentations. On top of the events we aim to run prize draws and develop an active mailing list/forum. We will support the Graduate Development Community in London and promote London based Open Source Software projects where possible.

Who can join?

Membership is restricted to Software Engineers with an interest in Front End technologies working in or around London (or those hoping to train into these technologies, or relocate to London). 

Is there a fee to join, is there a fee for the events?

It’s completely free to join and our events will be completely free.

How do I join?

Just click on the link on this page to sign up to the mailing list, you'll hear of all of our latest news and events and can take part in the monthly prize draws.

Do you have to go to every presentation?

Absolutely not - it’s completely up to you which events you attend and which you don’t. Every event attracts a different crowd.


Barry Cranford
Founder of Front Endgineers

name: London Spark Coding Dojo
description:
Apache Spark collaborative coding session. 

Each Dojo, is an opportunity to work in groups, on specific challenges. 

The goal is to learn, while connecting with fellow members of the London Spark coding community. 

The meet up, is open to all, regardless of your Spark skills, all you need is a laptop.

name: KNIME User Group UK
description: The KNIME User Group UK has the purpose of promoting the awareness, use and adoption of KNIME, the open source predictive analytics platform from www.knime.org. Membership and meetup attendance is open to all KNIME users, those interested in KNIME, as well as those interested in extending their analytics capability. The aim is to hold meetups where real-life experiences of using KNIME are aired, new developments in KNIME are explained with some deep dives into KNIME capabilities. As an open analytics platform, KNIME can work with R, WEKA and many other tools - the interoperability of KNIME will also be covered. The objective is to build a connected community of KNIME users and all those interested in analytics. Join up, and find out who else is interested in KNIME. Meetups will initially be held in London. If there is enough interest, we hope to have additional meetups in other parts of the UK. If you have a story around KNIME or analytics - please contact us.

name: Rust London User Group
description: A meetup for the interesting programming language Rust from Mozilla.

name: WebRTC - crossing borders
description:
As part of a community who believe that WebRTC is a movement for the next years, we exchange ideas, knowledge and experience, projects on where and how to apply this new future focused browser-to-browser technology.
Join the enthousiasts about new technologies and business related opportunities. 


This P2P communication in the browser is conquering EU; we zoom in on Belgium & Spain!
Only +/- 3 hours seperates us from Amsterdam, Berlin, Paris, Madrid, London, Dublin,... Istambul.
Let’s cross the borders & launch an open (EU->global) ecosystem!
Ambitious as we are, we invite you to get connected. Meetups can be held in Europe ; we kickoff on a boat in Gent, Antwerp and Brussels will follow; next pitstop will be a bar in Madrid ;)

Propose a talk: http://goo.gl/forms/a0s27wBnxL

You can follow the latest updates on https://twitter.com/WebRTCmeetup .

name: Epsom Tableau User Group Meetup
description:
If you use Tableau in a professional environment and are willing to share your experience then this group is for you.
We will explore the tool's functionality by working through real examples and publish some cool stuff with the wider Tableau community.

name: Digital Body Data - BodiMEetup
description:
BodiMEetup is informal think-tank to network, promote and discuss the fast growing Digital Body Data World and its future. During a series of regular talks we want to bring together startup founders, researcher, executives, investors and influencers to share their stories and opinions and discuss how to engaged community of entrepreneurial and forward-thinking leaders.

We believe our digital body is at the centre of our digital future, from avatar to mini-me statues, from fashion technology to bespoke tailor, from jewels to 3D printed organs.

name: [ Contain ]
description:
There are a wide variety of container technologies. But what should you deploy for your use-case and how do you get the most value out of it?

At Contain, understand how to use containers in practice, watch live demos and industry leading presentations, share ideas with peers.

name: London Linux
description: Everything about Linux

name: Cireson UK Community
description:
The Cireson UK Community is established to discuss, share and collaborate on all things Cireson & System Center. We have had significant interest in creating a forum to cover Cireson release updates and roadmap, service management, asset management, self-service automation & case studies.

Most importantly we will have customers and partners sharing implementations, best practices, hindsight and even service request automation runbooks to fast-track implementations and provide ideas for automation and self-service.

name: London Python Project Nights
description:
London Python Project Nights is a monthly event for people who code. 

The event's founders needed an excuse to find time to work on the ideas they always spoke about when they met at other tech events, but never found the time; they also thought this was probably a problem other developers faced, and that the added peer pressure of sharing their creations from conception would help them actually produce their projects. As a result London Python Project Nights was born. 

We welcome anyone who has a project idea they would like to work on, or looking for a project to contribute to. We have had people come to start a new project, people working on their existing project, people joining those of other attendees, even people coming to work alone on large well-known open source products. 

We do not enforce a minimum level of coding ability, but we do expect everyone to contribute on some level, and have a code of conduct we expect attendees to adhere to (http://london-python-project-nights.github.io/code-of-con...). This is intended to make the event as inclusive as possible, and suggestions for ways we can improve are welcome. 

TL;TR 

In summary we're all about code, everyone is welcome, bring your own food and drink, work on whatever you want, as long as you're willing to talk people through what you've done at the end. To keep in contact between events we have set up ldnpyprj.slack.com - anyone on gmail or hotmail should be able to sign up without an invite, let us know if you want to join but can't.

name: Software Technology Meetup
description:
A group focussed on software development. What is required to produce good ethical software that fulfils the customers needs and also benefits society as a whole. Software that does not do harm if it breaks. Software that is not tested on the user.

We are looking particularly for people involved directly in software development: programmers; analysts; project managers; app developers. They need to have a strong desire to understand how to make better software. People who are evangelical about quality assurance and governance.

You can make a difference to the way software is delivered.

name: London Data Products and Smart Applications Meetup
description:
we will make data products. 
we will review and invent design patterns in smart applications 
we will learn techniques in machine learning and data science like ensembles, deep learning

name: Meetup Mashup London
description: Interested in Internet of Things? Wearables? Big Data? Analytics? Machine Learning? Data Visualisation? Open Data initiatives? FinTech? Cloud-computing? How about bringing all of these together to develop innovative, disruptive, creative solutions? If that sounds interesting then this group is for you.

name: London μServices (Microservices) User Group
description:
The Architectural Monolith’s days are numbered. As companies are becoming more and more agile, and see how they can now adapt in order to innovate and compete faster than their competition, software development teams are being forced to maintain and evolve large, monolithic applications at a pace of change that those architectures were never meant to withstand, let alone embrace!

Microservices are a new approach to architecting applications. They are simple, single-purpose, lightweight architectural components that enable you to deliver software faster. The microservice architectural approach also aims to lead to software that thrives on change while at the same time being secure, performant, and stable.

This meet up is for people interested in architecting, designing, deploying and maintaining micro service based software architectures.

If you want to advertise jobs to the user group, read our policy here http://www.meetup.com/London-Microservices-User-Group/pages/Posting_Jobs_to_the_User_Group/

Follow us on twitter -> https://twitter.com/microservicesUG

Organised by Simplicity Itself - http://www.simplicityitself.io/community.html

name: Business, Analytics and Data Science
description:
An Industry first, where businesses (established and start-ups) and organisations come together in the spirit of innovation to discuss Business/Use cases and best practices in relation to the world of Data Science. Come to share, learn, keep up to date with the latest news and developments and meet real Data Scientists and Businesses at the cutting edge this exciting and brave new world.

We would also like to take the opportunity to thank our Sponsors DataIQ for supporting our meetup group and making this exciting venture possible.

Here's a short video from our meetup on 11 February 2016


https://youtu.be/IgjtkuIIZ58

name: Nordic APIs, London
description: This group is for anyone interesting in making the world more programmable, automated, mobile and efficient using APIs, open data, cloud services, and apps. We talk about API security, design, platforms, business models, marketing and strategy. We do this at after-work meetups, half-day conferences, and at an annual multi-day event. We also gather more frequently and informally at various other related events. We always hanging out in cyberspace and find each other using the hashtag #nordicapis.

name: HackTrain - Innovating at 200km/h
description: HackTrain is a network of innovators and technologists that are ready to evangelise the railway industry. An initiative to bring innovation to the railway industry through a series of immersive and unique meetups, hackathons and accelerators. What makes the HackTrain hackathon unique is our thorough focus on impact in the industry. The HackTrain brings together the world's most driven, skilled, and bold developers, designers and entrepreneurs, and provides them with an immersive environment to build high-impact solutions to solve burning problems in the industry. This, together with the help of our industry partners, ignites creativity, and allows our Trainhackers to conceive, build and launch scalable startups that provide scalable long-term solutions that have the potential to grow and truly have an impact on the world. Crazy? Definitely! Impossible? Not even close! HackTrain alumni have managed to build prototypes at the hackathon that reached headlines in high profile news headlines, exited by selling to railway companies, obtained access as advisors to boards in railway companies, and continued growing their projects forward. Nothing can stop innovation when travelling at 200km/h.

name: eCommerce Technology London
description:
We are a group of keen technology enthusiasts, professionals and developers, working within eCommerce and basically thought it would be a great idea to create a meetup group to meet more people from a similar background, share information and knowledge and open that up to others with similar interests. 

We are planning on hosting regular events, be they talks about eCommerce, what's new in various technologies, as well as meeting for social occasions.

Anyone is welcome to attend who has an interest or works within eCommerce technology, and we certainly welcome anyone who would like to present to us. Just get in touch with Kate (organiser of the meetup group) for further details.

We are kindly sponsored by MetaPack, but happy to partner with others in our field.

We're looking forward to welcoming you to your first event with us.

name: FBX Tech Empowerment London
description: Supporting appropriate, open tech for non-profits and people. We're a diverse group welcoming diverse participants to practical workshops on open tech and privacy skills, tech design and discussion workshops. We're interested in the practices, politics and theory of new technologies and want everyone to have the skills and knowledge they need be a safer, more empowered, tech user.

name: London Cyber Security
description:
Anyone interested in improving their organisations network security. We will get speakers from leading companies covering topics such as cyber security incident response, cyber forensics, information security, breach detection, and network incident visualisation + much much more ;)
Come along if you want to get knowledge from security Jedis tackling the dark side of cyber space! (Padawans welcome ... even Sith lords) [that's enough star wars references now ... Ed.]

name: London Enterprise Technology Meetup
description: The LNETM fosters innovation in the London enterprise technology ecosystem through promoting early stage technology companies, supporting entrepreneurs, educating companies on how to work with enterprises, and creating an environment where entrepreneurs, investors, and businesses can all network and learn from one another. Check out our latest news at www.lnetm.com where you can also request to present.

name: Cloud Natives
description: developers, engineers, architects and ops people interested the latest infrastructure tools and tech stacks, methods and people. what's the new hotness and why?

name: Elastic London User Group
description: This group is for anyone interested in open source search, logging, analytics & data visualization. We primarily focus on four open source projects — Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana, and Beats — but we welcome talks on any aspect of data exploration.

name: Big Data London
description:
Welcome to Big Data London - Europe's biggest Big Data community. Big Data London brings together people working on Big Data projects.

If you're using Hadoop, Apache Cassandra or any other NoSQL related technology, if you're involved with web apps, enterprise apps, data analytics, financial apps or storage at massive scale, or simply want to learn more about the space, then you'll find something interesting here.

So come and join us.

name: Ionic UK Meetup Group
description:
This is the official UK meetup group for the Ionic SDK. 

This Meetup is for anyone using or interested in using the Ionic, a beautiful, open source front-end SDK for developing hybrid mobile apps with HTML5.

We welcome attendees of all skill levels and would love to hear about projects and apps that you are working on. 

If you would like to present something related to Ionic at an upcoming event, please email us at ionicuk@gmail.com


-- Code of Conduct --

Ionic UK is dedicated to providing a harassment-free conference experience for everyone, regardless of gender, gender identity and expression, age, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, or religion (or lack thereof). We do not tolerate harassment of event participants in any form. Sexual language and imagery is not appropriate for any conference venue, including talks, workshops, parties, Twitter and other online media. Event participants violating these rules may be sanctioned or expelled from the event and all future event at the discretion of the organisers. (adapted from confcodeofconduct.com)

name: Firefox OS London
description:
If you interested in Firefox OS ,HTML5, JS, mobile and the open web? Get together with other developers, open web advocates and people passionate about mobile to talk about how we can keep the web free, share best practise and more.

It doesn't matter if you are an experienced coder or just want to learn more, everyone is welcome :) We'll be running meetups, hangouts, tutorials and maybe even hackday in the future, so come join us!

name: The digital asset legal meetup
description:
This is a group based in London for anyone interested in the legal principles applicable to digital property rights and the business models associated with cloud computing. Depending on interest, the meetups could include talks and workshops about recent developments in the field, or just friendly conversation.

The group is aimed at legal and other professionals involved in advising clients about the administration of the property rights associated with digital information and digital asset management. Proprietors of businesses using or providing cloud services could also find the discussions useful in the conduct of their businesses. Finally, trustees, personal representatives, court of protection deputies and other fiduciaries using cloud services would benefit from involvement in the discussions of the group.

name: London FileMaker Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in starting using or developing in FileMaker Pro. We aim to support someone who just started in database development or just researching on a suitable development platform. If you are a seasoned FileMaker developer, you should probably look up one of the existing user groups.

name: Natural Language Understanding
description:
Natural Language Understanding is a meetup that brings together developers who are interested in or are working on incorporating NLU into their mobile or IoT solution. We will present various tools and platforms available to incororate NLU into mobile or web products and facilitate hackathons to play with tech.

A single line description of NLU from wikipedia:
Natural language understanding is a subtopic of natural language processing in artificial intelligence that deals with machine reading comprehension.

name: London Systematic Traders
description:
This meet-up group is for anyone who has an interest, works in or wants to learn more about systematic, algorithmic (i.e. automated) or quantitative trading applied to any type of financial instrument including Forex, Indices, Equities, Commodities or indeed anything else that can be traded.

This community is open to researchers, recruiters, backtesters, quantitative developers and traders. By establishing this group we hope to:

1. Build a community within which to discuss and exchange of ideas, know-how and best practices relating to all aspects of algorithmic trading

2. Enable the building of networks between traders, software developers and researchers

3. Facilitate the sharing of knowledge, between community members via talks, presentations, debates and discussion of research topics. We are not platform or broker specific and we warmly welcome all members of the research, development and trading community to participate in our events.

We plan to develop an online community (including online discussions within the meet-up group) and to then subsequently organise social events, seminars and possible workshops depending on the level of interest.

name: Future of Data: London
description: This meetup is focused on the Future of Data and the open community data projects governed by the Apache Software Foundation. Geared towards developers, data scientists and ALL Data enthusiasts who are building modern data applications. Our meetups cover all data -- data-in-motion and data-at-rest.  Meetups provide an opportunity to listen, share and work hands on with other technologists in the open source and open community Apache tools.

name: Online Lending Meetup (P2P lending)
description:
We bring together a community online lending investors (lenders) and people working in the industry. 

At each meetup, experts will provide valuable insight and open discussions.

The goal is to learn more on this fast-growing asset class and share ideas. 

It’s an opportunity to discuss about a diverse range of topics, from the lending platforms themselves and underlying product, to risk management, through to taxes issues, technology and more.

name: Analytics.Club London
description:
Join Analytics.Club, one of the world fastest growing community of data science professionals. It is geared towards establishing effective networks across data science communities. The focus of the meetup is around 'All Things Analytics' best practices, use cases, latest trends and cutting edge technologies to help professionals stay ahead, stay connected and stay informed. 

Also join Analytics.Club [Global Network of Data Analytics Professionals]

name: Meteor London
description: Meet other developers using Meteor. Share your knowledge, apps, and get feedback from others. Meteor is an open-source platform for building top-quality web apps in a fraction of the time, whether you're an expert developer or just getting started.

name: Hadoop Users Group UK
description: We are the Hadoop users group for the UK based in London. We meet monthly for talks and discussion on all topics related to Hadoop. Join if you're interested in learning what Hadoop is, how people are using it with their big data problems, and to meet other people with experience running and coding on Hadoop cluster around London and the UK.

name: Ubuntu Meetup
description: Find Ubuntu users and events from all over the country, come and join the Ubuntu UK Local Community Team.

name: Serverless London
description: A group for anyone interested in building web, mobile and Internet-of-Things applications with serverless architectures using the Serverless Framework and more! We'll focus heavily on Amazon Web Services and discuss AWS Lambda as the focal point of AWS.

name: OpenAI London
description:
Hi, my name is Renat. I started this meetup group because I want to help OpenAI fulfill its mission (I’m not affiliated with the OpenAI non-profit organization). When I was in college, the world of artificial intelligence fascinated me. So I was applying Neural Nets to data sets generated by e-commerce websites (using Kohonen’s Self Organizing Maps).

It was 1999. Looking back, I realize that my research is a joke compared to what you can do today.

What becomes possible tomorrow is super exciting and scary at the same time. That is why I decided to contribute my time and evangelize importance of this non-profit organization among artificial intelligence enthusiasts in London. Specifically, I will be finding and securing physical locations where members of this group could meet in person, share and discuss ideas.

If you care to help - drop me a line with any ideas or suggestions you might have. Or simply say hello and introduce yourself because I would like to learn about you and the projects you are working on! See you soon!

Disclaimer: This Meetup group is not affiliated with the OpenAI non-profit organization. This Meetup group does not own the OpenAI trademark; this Meetup has no affiliation, connection or association with such third party; Such third party has not approved nor sponsored this Meetup group's use of the trademark in any way.

name: London Cloud Foundry User Group (LCFUG) Meetup
description: “This is a group for anyone interested in developing and deploying applications at speed through the use of Cloud Foundry PaaS, underpinned by Cloud Foundry BOSH. All skills levels are welcome and all technical disciplines, Ops folk, Developers, IaaS admins, Unix sysadmins etc are welcome. I started this group to create a focal point on the ever growing use of CF and PaaS. Looking forward to catching up with everybody.”

name: London Web Components Meetup
description: A group for those who are interested in the future of the web, Web Components hope to enable developers to create richer web applications and sites with reusable, easy to implement methods. The technology will cover HTML, JavaScript, CSS and complementary frameworks like Polymer & X-tags. Join us for presentations & conversations from experts using and shaping this technology.

name: B.U.I.L.D business networking and more London
description:
B.U.I.L.D (Businesses United​ ​for Innovation, Learning and Development) is set up to offer more opportunities for people with an entrepreneurial mindset to learn from each other and build successful businesses. Together.

Why join B.U.I.L.D?

If you are looking to participate in events like workshops, trainings, lectures, seminars, hackathons aiming to transform you and your business for success and you consider yourself a business B.U.I.L.D:er, it would be foolish of you not to join this group.

A business B.U.I.L.D:er is:

·  anyone who wants to build a successful business;

·  somebody who has an entrepreneurial mindset = often drawn to opportunities, innovation, new value creation and willing to take risks

·  an employee curious about starting a business or wanting to apply entrepreneurial thinking at his/her workplace.

·  a smart manager or business owner looking for innovation ideas,

·  an edgy consultant, freelancer or solopreneur

·  a student or researcher with an entrepreneurship interest

Do you see value and opportunities in networking and want business dreams to come true in mutually beneficial ways? Invest in yourself and a more entrepreneurial world today and come along!

What is a B.U.I.L.D event?

B.U.I.L.D events can be about sales, marketing, branding, customer engagement, self development, finance, law, growth hacking and any other topic which in one way or another can help businesses become more awesome.

Become an event organizer

• You can attend events and benefit from networking with likeminded. However, your benefits can be massive if you organize these events yourself. Events and Meetup groups are a great way to get:

• connections

• promote your services and expertise

• goodwill 

• test ideas

• feedback

• referrals 

• introductions

Being part of a bigger organization and group opens more doors than going about it alone. B.U.I.L.D exists in 11 cities in Europe. 

Running a successful Meetup-group also requires, much like a business, grit and a lot of time, dedication and effort. What if you could go in lean and test your session by organizing only one event?

We at B.U.I.L.D give you a chance to organize just one event (or more in the future) under the B.U.I.L.D. brand with its existing members instead of starting your own Meetup group from scratch.

How to apply

If you would like to promote your service by sharing your knowledge and expertise with other professionals and entrepreneurs with a workshop or get-together; apply to get your event published and promoted by contacting EntAnon's Community Manager Jenny via e-mail on jenny.bjorklof@entanon.com. You get support on how to organize great B.U.I.L.D events by experienced business event organizers.

Please note: Free events = free support, paid events = agreed profit share on a case to case basis.

The history of B.U.I.L.D

B.U.I.L.D is a brand by EntAnon (short for Entrepreneurs Anonymous). In 2015 more than 30 thought provoking events were organized by EntAnon and B.U.I.L.D (that is at least one event every second week) engaging thousands of members.  

The name Entrepreneurs Anonymous could stand for being addicted to Entrepreneurship and having an urgent need to get group support for it. But actually Entrepreneurs Anonymous is more about providing a safe place with like-minded people where entrepreneurship can be explored. Here Entrepreneurs-to-be and undercover entrepreneurs from corporates have been spotted too. 

Entrepreneurs Anonymous events started in Dublin, Ireland in 2011 as accountability group by former students of an entrepreneurship course. The interest for the group grew and now social events with guest speakers are organized every last Tuesday of the month. With a membership increase by 10% each month it was quickly realized last Tuesday-events were simply just not enough for the Anonymous Entrepreneurs.

B.U.I.L.D was set up to offer more opportunities for Entrepreneurs to learn from each other. So far B.U.I.L.D events like the Gigonomy Panel discussion, Speed Business Networking and the Free Business Clinic have been organized. B.U.I.L.D also organizes former DDM events. These are events for people especially interested in Data Driven Marketing. 

More about B.U.I.L.D and DDM Alliance

EntAnon's brand ​​B.U.I.L.D partnered ​ with the former Data Driven Marketing Alliance (DDM). Future ​DDM ​meetups and other events in Copenhagen, Berlin, Belgium, Dublin, Dusseldorf, Helsinki, London, Manchester, Netherlands, Paris, Stockholm, ​soon ​Milano​ and other parts of Europe will be organized together with B.U.I.L.D. DDM representatives​ can ​set up online events​ ​(webinars and conferences) and use the B.U.I.L.D. groups around Europe ​as ​​a channel. If another B.U​.​I​.​L​.​D or EntAnon​ ​event is set on the same date the organizers agree​ ​on the next best date for the DDM Alliance event to take​ ​place.

name: London Streams
description: Have you ever wondered how Netflix delivers movies to your home with a flick of a tile? or how Twitter keeps your tweets flowing to deliver you breaking news? or how Tesla knows when to notify its drivers when to service their electric vehicle? If so, join us in this exciting new meetup to uncover the mysteries of continuous data flows and how to build robust stream computing environments. We're looking for speakers, enthusiasts, hackers, and innocent bystanders to join us for food and drink in and around your area.

name: BITNATION
description: Bitnation provides all the services a traditional government provides, from law and insurance to security - but in a geographically unbound, decentralised and voluntary way. Bitnation is powered by the blockchain technology, a cryptographically secured public ledger distributed amongst all of its users.

name: FINtank
description: Join us, as we get together for intelligent conversation about technology and innovation within the Financial, Banking & Insurance sectors. This group would be most relevant to professionals which hold C-level, managerial, director, IT infrastructure, digital change management and consultancy roles as well as other FINTECH leaders.

name: Social Data London
description: This is a group for anyone interested in, working with or researching social media data. Rather then putting the emphasis on the technology itself, we'll focus on how social data is currently being used by brands, designers, public organisations, artists, government and academia. We'll meet once every two months in Central London (Baker St tube) and you are welcome to join us.

name: Big Data Jobs in London
description:
This is a networking group for those interested in Big Data & the Cloud.

It is open to all Big Data and Cloud specialists in London who like to share their experiences and ideas.

 

Organised by eSynergy Solutions, an IT recruitment company based in the heart of the City. 

In early 2012 we set up a Cloud and Big Data division  specialising in recruiting for contract and permanent Big Data technical positions.

We work with Big Data Vendors, Specialised Consulting companies and end user clients to find exceptional candidates with Big Data technical and managerial skills.

If you are looking for a new role, or are looking to hire staff, we can help.

name: Graduate Data Science Initiative
description:
The Graduate Data Science Initiative (GDSI) is an initiative that aims to create an environment where students both undergraduates and graduates can learn about data science at an introductory, intermediate, and/or advanced level. The initiative's main objective is to equip students with the right skills to enter the growing and expanding market of data science.

 

As a member of the GDSI you will be able to learn about the different tools, methods, and technologies being used within the data science community. You will be exposed to real-world use case scenarios of data science in the industry and academia. You will learn about how machine learning is used to predict stock market trends, how natural language processing is used to determine the sentiment on a particular topic, how programming languages like R, Clojure, and Python are leading the way in performing data analysis, how NoSQL databases are providing a new paradigm to store unstructured data retrieved from social networks, sensors, log files, etc., how technologies like Hadoop are revolutionising data processing and parallel computing, how recommendations systems work inside Amazon, Netflix, Spotify, how DNA sequencing is being facilitated by machine learning algorithms, how data mining is helping in better understanding human-environment interactions and social economic dynamics, how predictive analytics is helping today's business leaders in making key decisions and transforming their businesses into huge success stories and many more.

 

Besides the intellectual juice we'll provide with a warm and welcoming social environment.

 

FAQ

What are the events organized by GDSI like?

The events usually include technical presentations on topics relevant to Data Science at an introductory/intermediate/or advanced level. They are followed by a networking session where members can have the chance to enjoy friendly conversations.

Do I need to have prior technical/programming knowledge to join the GDSI?

No programming knowledge is required to attend our events. The events are dedicated to people coming from a range of disciplines and experiences with a passion for data science.

Is there a membership fee?

Joining the GDSI is absolutely free.

What do I benefit by joining the GDSI?

You will have the opportunity to learn about cutting edge technologies and industry practices currently being applied in Big Data projects across a range of industry sectors. Furthermore, you will have the chance to meet interesting people and forge new contacts that will prove to be valuable in the future for your personal and career development.

How do I register for an event?

To register for an event you must first join our meetup group. You can do that by clicking on the 'Join Us' button on the top-right corner. After you join us, you will be able to explore future events and add yourself to the attendees list. It's that simple!

Do check our blog at http://graduatedatascience.com/

You can also follow us on Twitter @graduate_dsi


Fatos Ismali

Founder of the Graduate Data Science Initiative.

name: London Puppet User Group
description:
Join the London Puppet User Group (PUG) to gather with other Puppet users, and hear talks on Puppet, Configuration Management, and DevOps!

Puppet is IT automation software that helps system administrators manage infrastructure throughout its lifecycle, from provisioning and configuration to patch management and compliance. Using Puppet, you can easily automate repetitive tasks, quickly deploy critical applications, and proactively manage change, scaling from 10s of servers to 1000s, on-premise or in the cloud.

All participants are expected to follow Puppet Labs' code of conduct: bit.ly/eventconduct

If you would like to talk please send an email to fiona@puppetlabs.com with the following

• Name 

• Company (optional) 

• Any contact info 

• (Twitter, Github etc) 

• Level of user talk is aimed at 

• Short blurb about the talk

name: Polish Developers in London
description:
This group has been created to bring together Polish developers living in London - a chance to discuss technology, home affairs and just enjoy the company of each other.  This group is run by Adam Bolton and Magdalena Marczak, and we look forward to seeing you!


Ta grupa została stworzona z myślą o polskich developerach mieszkających w Londynie, by stworzyć im okazję do podyskutowania na temat technologii, spraw wewnętrznych lub po prostu zachęcić do spędzenia czasu w ciekawym towarzystwie. Grupa prowadzona jest przez Adama Boltona oraz Magdalenę Marczak. Serdecznie zapraszamy!

name: London Unikernels
description: Unikernels are single-purpose library operating systems custom-built to run a single application directly on the hypervisor. Compared to typical VMs in the cloud running complete operating systems, unikernels offer superior security and simplicity. This group is for anyone interested in unikernel implementations.

name: RE.WORK Future & Emerging Technology
description:
RE.WORK combines entrepreneurship, technology and science to solve some of the world's greatest challenges using emerging technology. We showcase the opportunities of exponentially accelerating technologies and their impact on business and society. 

Emerging technology is providing an unprecedented era of opportunity for entrepreneurs and scientists to progress business and solve global challenges. Do you know how to leverage new technologies such as the internet of things, sensors, 3D printing, nanotechnology, biotechnology, artificial intelligence? How can you apply emerging research to solve our biggest challenges such as unprecedented urbanisation levels, efficient healthcare, education for all, sustainable energy solutions and food for all?

name: Technopreneurs - Tech Startups and Entrepreneurs
description:
We are a group of IT professionals, web startups and entrepreneurs. 

This group is for all those who not only want to become part of the meetup but also want to participate. We give you opportunity to speak and also participate. 

Let's become part of our team. Join us, become part of our team and let's expand together. Let's build connections and let's retain them by attending our upcoming events.

name: AWS User Group UK
description:
A meetup group to coordinate a face-to-face AWS user community. Proposed topics will be more about the technical aspects of AWS feature use and implementation, and will feature real-world use cases including what hasn't worked as well as what has. Join if you're a cloud evangelist in your organisation, and you design implement or service AWS based solutions.

All abilities are welcome, but be prepared to get in-depth!

name: London NATS Cloud Native User Group
description: NATS (NATS.io) was created by Derek Collison, founder and CEO of Apcera, who has spent 20+ years designing, building, and using publish-subscribe messaging systems. This group is for those in the London area interested in building modern, reliable and scalable cloud and distributed systems.

name: AnalogFolk London Hack Festival
description:
Who should join?
Creative thinkers, designers, makers, hackers, entrepreneurs and coding ninjas are welcome to join this Meetup group. If you have a passion for making digital products to solve real world problems then this is the group for you.

Why should members join?
This Meetup group facilitates the bringing together talented individuals (See 'Who should join?' above) to learn, network and ultimately make products and services; using digital solutions to make the analog world better.

What can members expect out of the group?
The group will arrange Meetups to work collaboratively, learn, play with the latest hardware and gadgets and network with the best technical and creative thinkers in London.

Community
AnalogFolk will schedule and host the Meetups. All the members of the group have to do is attend and have fun.

name: London Virtual Data Science Meetup
description: A series of webinars and London based meetups focusing on Data Science, Deep Learning and their practical, commercial applications

name: London and South East Big Data Meetup
description: Looking for all Big data enthusiasts! This is a group for anyone interested in data and big data in all its beauty. Its an open forum to enable people to discuss all the various incarnations of big data and the technologies that can/will support it. We will look at Hadoop for sure (cloudera, hortonworks, EMR, etc.), Amazon (and all its various bits and pieces - S3, Aurora, DynamoDB, etc.), Azure (and its varied offerings - HDInsight, etc.) as well as other new big data technologies (Spark, Solr, Vertica, etc.) . We will meet once a month in Holborn areas as its so central - will look for a bar - 5 - 8pm. A few ideas and open discussion at the start and on with networking and beer drinking.

name: Social Data
description:
This is a meetup about the use of social data.

Like me you may be wanting to use Social data (aka Social media data, big data, unstructured data) to drive insight.

You may be asking questions like:

    What social data should I use and why?

    What can I learn from others who have used social data successfully in their organization?

    What are the key trends in the use of social data?

    Where can I meet with social data publishers face to face?

    What tools can I leverage to analyze?

    How do I integrate social data into my organization?

It's all very well hooking into the Twitter streams and collecting a bunch of Facebook likes but what do we do with the data when we've got it?

So no matter whether you're a budding social media marketing guru, a data scientist, a Chief Data Officer, or a product czar - this meetup is for you.

name: hackameetup
description: Here at hackameetup, we're all about three things - Beers, Pizza and Hackers. We meet once a fortnight bringing along CTO's, industry experts and awesome companies. Our group is for all tech enthusiasts, coders and non-coders and is a great opportunity to meet likeminded people and chat with some of the best and brightest in the community. We look forward to seeing you soon.

name: Go Hackers London
description: We’re the London-based GoLang Hacker group. Go Hackers London is a meetup with a simple purpose: Code together, on anything. We welcome all skill levels, backgrounds, ages, genders, you name it. Come and hack on anything you want to do with Golang, alone or in a group. Learn from others, or teach others.

name: STEM Talks at King's College London
description: This is a group for anyone interested in STEM subjects delivered by academics from the Faculty of Natural & Mathematical Sciences at King's College London and our corporate partners.

name: London BIM 4 Analysis Meetup Group
description: This is a group for anyone interested in the latest developments and applications of Building Information Modelling and how it applies to performance analysis for the optimised design and operation of buildings. We will have industry and academic speakers come to present findings from their projects and research. This group will be of interest to Architects, Engineers, Environmental Consultants, building designers, BREEAM assessors, LEED AP, IESVE users, Revit users and students.

name: TechXperts
description: TechXperts provides a platform for IT professionals to come together and interact with today's leading technology vendors. Our aim is to create a strong network for discussion, collaboration and the sharing of ideas around Infrastructure, Middleware, Database and IT Management technologies.

name: Pivotal London - Cloud Native Apps Meetup
description:
Platform as a Service (PaaS) is the here and now for devops focused cloud native apps. Pivotal Cloud Foundry is the core technology behind many popular PaaS solutions on the market from IBM, HP etc. This user group brings together people who are involved, using or want to know about Cloud Foundry and other agile technology from Pivotal.  

This is a group for anyone interested in a more agile approach to developing, deploying, managing and updating the innovative new cloud-native applications which modern businesses needs to survive and thrive. 

People should join this group if they write application code or manage/run/work in IT operations that use or may want to use Cloud Foundry. Its a chance to hear latest news and trends, share stories, learn with hands on experience and network with other Pivotal users. We aim to  have regular meet-ups focusing on specific industries. you can expect to attend hands-on workshops, seminars and talks from Cloud Foundry users and developers.

name: CoreOS London
description: A meetup around CoreOS - Linux for Massive Server Deployments

name: School of Commoning Events
description:
We are a commons education group based in London, established as a Community Interest Company under UK law.

What is the Commons?

“The social and political space where things get done and where people have a sense of belonging and have an element of control over their lives, providing sustenance, security and independence... Commons are organized around resources that are collectively owned or shared between or among populations. These resources are said to be held in common and can include everything from natural resources to domains of the cultural sphere, e.g.: literature, music, arts, design, film, video, television, radio, information, software and sites of heritage. The commons can also include ‘public goods’ such as public space, public education, health and the infrastructure that allows our society to function (such as electricity or water delivery systems). There also exists the ‘life commons’, e.g. the human genome.” (Wikipedia)


Our Purpose

To benefit society by enhancing individual and collective competences in the protection, governance, and cultivation of commons, as an autonomous partner to the private and public sectors.

name: Bioinformatics London
description: This is a group for anyone interested in Bioinformatics, Machine Learning apply to biological data, Multi-omics, Next Generation Sequencing, etc. Bioinformatician, Computation Biologist, People has Machine Learning background, Experimentalist who want to know more about bioinformatics, etc, are welcome. I started this group to meet other biological data analyst.

name: Open IoT London
description: Discussing and experimenting with the Internet of Things via open standards, open data, open source, open hardware and open radio. For hobbyists, makers, hackers, academics and mad scientists!

name: Ember London
description:
Ember London is a community for anyone interested in Ember.js and building ambitious applications in the browser.

We host monthly meetups with talks from contributors, library authors and enthusiasts. The aim is to cover a broad range of topics of interest to beginners and advanced users alike.

name: London SDN & OpenDaylight User Group
description:
This is a group for anyone interested in Software Defined Networking, OpenDaylight, Openflow and related technologies like OpenStack etc. All skill levels, network enthusiasts are welcome, whether your are technical, non-technical business folk, or an entrepreneur…

It’s to debate and share experiences on all things SDN, including; hardware, switching, the OpenFlow protocol, controllers, application concepts, industry hype and reality, use cases, business adoption, and many other things…

name: TensorFlow London
description:
Does TensorFlow have the potential to become the engine behind most successful consumer and industrial products of the next 10-20 years? 

Absolutely! A much better question is how, and in what new ways, can we:

a) train more computers to teach themselves by sifting through massive amounts of data coming out of all sorts of places

b) make these computers available through an API to provide a high-quality answer to anyone who is in need. 


Why? Because everyone in need deserves the right answer. 

So.... why don't we standardize & democratize the field with and around TensorFlow, and help change the world!?

What. We are a local micro community of those interested in advancing their knowledge of TensorFlow, its use cases and applications.

How. Join our group for a regular dose of human interaction, conversations, smiles, food and drinks on all things TensorFlow:

• How-To's & Best Practices

• Tutorials

• Models

• Algorithms

• Multi-GPU Autoscaling in the cloud

• Tools & Integrations

We will learn how others solve some of the hard problems that exist in the world around us, and how others make predictive APIs and  applications 

Join the movement. Let’s change the world. 

Because everyone in need deserves the right answer.

You are welcome:)

name: Innovate London
description:
This is a group for anyone interested in hearing about the latest and coolest technologies (Wearables, Internet of Things, Beacons, Arduino, 3D Printing, RaspberryPi, Intel Edison, I.A., Augmented Reality, etc). 

Maybe you are into NodeJS and game development (Corona, Unity) or you just want to showoff your awesome GitHub repo or latest app, Its a place where everyone can share their work, learn new things and get to talk with like-minded people. 

Another goal of the meetup is organize hackathons from time to time and also get surprise guests at every event. Did i mention there will be beer and prizes?

name: London SQL Meetup for Database professionals
description:
If your job involves looking after your organisation's databases, and you know that while the core applications run nicely on Oracle or MySQL, and the BI tools are running on SQL Server, and it won't be long until a new application comes along which requires a MongoDB, Hadoop or Cassandra infrastructure , then this group is for you.

Different tools for different purposes.  And you're expected to have knowledge of all them.  

Expert knowledge. 

24/7.  

365.

This group is there to educated and inform; to connect you to peers that are having similar challenges and can give you guidance; and to connect you to experts that have the luxury of time to get into the details of that latest feature of the newest version of whatever the database might be.

Please do join us.

name: Open Data Science Fellows Program
description:
Open Data Science Fellows Program (ODSFP) is for all of you who want to learn and apply data science. It is a collaborative platform to get together to learn data science, to solve meaningful open data problems, hang out, ask questions, share ideas and have a great time. This is a not-for-profit community program dedicated to the dissemination of data science and to promote open data for social good, organized by Persontyle School of Data Science. 

Open Data + Data Science = Social Good 

You will learn Data Science and apply it to solve real data challenges of social/charity/humanitarian organizations. Exciting opportunity for us to collaboratively engage with each other, the community and issues we care about, and our world. 

“The ability to take data — to be able to understand it, to process it, to extract value from it, to visualize it, to communicate it — that’s going to be a hugely important skill in the next decades.” - Hal Varian 

Follow the program on Twitter @ODSFP

Join the ODSFP LinkedIn Group 

More details about Meetups and Data Activism (If you want to organize Meetup in your country, city, campus, company, etc. Contact the organizer)

name: Fit Tech Summit
description:
Fit Tech Summit exists to help ‘facilitate FitTech businesses succeed with developing relevant products, raising finance and achieving scale to improve the wellbeing of all humans.’ 

We choose to fulfil some of these objectives by inviting in speakers to our monthly event in order to broaden the scope of discussion and debate, and we are grateful to you for any contribution you can make towards developing this space. 

Come and join the Fit Tech community!

name: London DevSecOps Meetup
description: We're putting Security in DevOps! The industry has chosen DevOps and Cloud Computing as the next revolution and found that the last frontier of Security stands in the way of greatness. We will meet to exchange and create new ideas on how to leverage the best of the DevOps and SecOps worlds and adopt a new mind-set of inclusiveness and collaboration. Join our events to learn more about a new way of achieving secure innovation at scale without the friction of manual methods and the limits of traditional security.

name: IoTDataViz London
description: As Data Visualization for the Internet of Things (IoT) is still only gaining momentum, there are huge opportunities for those looking to get involved. Join us in exploring the potential and roles that Data Visualization will play across IoT verticals and the resulting products and insights for business and consumers alike. For more information please visit: www.iotdataviz.com

name: The London MySQL Meetup Group
description: Meet MySQL users, developers and DBAs, learn about new technologies and features, share opinions, experience and knowledge - All in the London MySQL Meetup Group. For MySQL, MariaDB, Percona Server and other MySQL-related technologies.

name: IT ñ @UK
description:
Profesionales de las tecnologías de la información, hackers expatriados trabajando en el Reino Unido.

Nos gustaría reunir a todas aquellas personas que tienen pasión alrededor de las tendencias en tecnologías de la información, ya sea software, sistemas, metodologías, etc.

En Londres hay muchos grupos similares, y con éste queremos promocionar y conectar a los profesionales de habla hispana o que están interesados en el español como lengua vehicular.

Queremos proponer las actividades que hemos visto que son interesantes como:

- charlas

- coding dojos

name: London Kaggle Meetup
description: This is a group for anyone interested in getting involved in Kaggle competitions and meeting other people in the data science community. The goals are to get data and computer enthusiasts together to form groups to enter Kaggle competitions and discuss the latest tools & techniques available to the data science community. These goals will be accomplished by holding hackdays every few months, built around Kaggle competitions, and by having a monthly meetup in which users participate in small groups to discuss new ideas within data science or Kaggle competitions.

name: s9s Polyglot Persistence - London
description: This meetup is for all those database administrators, system admins, devops professionals etc who deal with multiple types of databases, and in particular MySQL, MongoDB and PostgreSQL. The purpose of this group is to provide talks and a discussion forums to share best practices and ideas on how best automate and manage mixed open source database environments.

name: App Engine
description:
Meet others interested in developing apps on Google App Engine.

This meetup has a strong programming focus, so talks showing working code and workarounds are actively encouraged.

Each meetup will have a reasonable amount of time for informal lightning talks to show members' work.

name: wp-hooked: WordPress Developer meetups in London
description:
WP-hooked is a forum/meetup for WordPress core contributors, theme and plugin developers to get together and share issues, ideas and tips about WordPress.

If your main interaction with WordPress is through the admin console, if it's something that you install and configure rather than build then this meetup probably isn't for you. There's a long-running "WordPress London" meetup which has a much broader scope and will probably give you what you need.

If on the other hand you relish the thought of getting stuck into writing some php code, you can handle using the theme editor on a live site as an option, or the thought of managing your own servers isn't terrifying, then you've probably come to the right place.

The format of the meetups has yet to be decided, and will evolve as we learn what works and what doesn't.

We welcome speakers from any sphere who can add something to our development

name: Maker Mile
description:
The MAKER MILE is one square mile of open workshops, tech startups, artist and design studios, fabricators, galleries, shops and businesses, centering along Vyner Street between Bethnal Green and London Fields stations. This Meetup is for the businesses and spaces in the Maker Mile to network, share, and communicate.

www.makermile.cc

if we have missed your organisation off the map please send a hi res photo, 300 word description and your address to makermilemap@gmail.com

name: How design saved my life
description:
